Commentary: Full and outside off, Harris takes his bat away from the line.

Huge shout for LBW. Broad wants it. He knows it is out. Or shall we say, he always knows it is out. He wants a review but Root is not too sure. Bairstow reckons it is going down the leg side. A length ball, around off, coming in, Harris looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads. Broad runs towards the keeper in celebration and then appeals towards the umpire. Dharmasena is ready to signal a leg bye but then waits on seeing the conference between the players. Eventually, signals a leg bye. Ball Tracker shows it to be going down leg.
Landed outside off, coming in a long way, Warner knows where his off stump is and lets it pass.

OUT! Caught behind! Broad gets Warner again! A wry smile from Warner as he mutters something like 'knicked it' to Harris while going past. Gosh. He cannot buy a run against Broad. The son of Chris Broad is flying. Just the start England would have wanted after being asked to bowl first. A length delivery wide outside off, could have been left alone but Warner wants to play at it. Wants to have a feel. Then, he realizes that this is just the first over and he can let it go. Too late. The ball takes the toe end and goes behind to Jonny Bairstow. One down in the opening over! This is the 10th time that Broad has dismissed Warner, most by any bowler. Also, 5th out of 7 meetings in this series!
Around middle, Labuschagne works it behind square leg for a single.
Outside off, coming in, let through. A sensational opening over from Broady!
Wide outside off to start off by Archer. A very slow ball to start off with, around 80 mph. Left alone by Labuschagne.
On the pads of Labuschagne, he tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball goes towards fine leg and the batters take a run.
Down the leg side, Harris tries to flick but it is way too wide for him to make any contact.
On the pads of Harris, he flicks it down towards the fine leg fielder and they take a single. He is off the mark with that one.
Length ball around off,  defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Outside off, left alone by Labuschagne. Gentle over by Archer to start off with.
FOUR! Beautiful drive! This is full and outside off, Harris just leans into his drive and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Harris shoulders arms to it.
Another length ball outside off, Harris pushes it with soft hands towards cover point and takes a quick single.
Good front foot defense by Marnus. Broad attacks the off pole with a fuller ball, the batter blocks it out off the front foot.

FOUR! Uppish but well short of Overton at squarish mid-wicket. On the pads of Marnus, he flicks the ball towards mid-wicket. Overton dives to his right in an attempt to stop the ball but he is a little bit away from it. The ball goes to the fence and a boundary is signalled.
Stifled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Dharmasena indicates that this has hit the bat of Labushagne as he tries to block it out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On a length and on middle and leg, Harris looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Fuller this time around off, Harris blocks it off the front foot and onto the pitch.
Length ball on the pads of Harris, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple.
Beaten! Great delivery by Archer. This is on a length outside off, Harris looks to defend but does so inside the line and is beaten as the ball goes past his outside edge.
This time Harris defends it well as he gets behind the line of this fullish delivery outside off and pushes it back.
Length ball outside off by Broad, Marnus leaves it alone.
Another length ball outside off, Labuschagne again leaves it alone. Looks like Broad is trying to use the wind to his advantage here in Manchester to get the ball to swing in to the right-hander.
Attacking the front pad of Marnus, Labuschagne flicks it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Wide outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
This is fuller and a bit outside off, Labuschagne blocks it out off the front foot onto the pitch.
This is way too wide for Labuschagne, he leaves it alone and Bairstow collects it behind the stumps.
Good shot off the front foot this by Harris. This is fuller and on middle and off, Harris pushes it towards mid on and takes a couple as Leach runs behind it and mops it up.
Harris blocks this one off the front foot by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Bouncer but way too high! Harris ducks under it and the ball goes over Bairstow's head. Bairstow leaps and gets a hand to it but he is not able to stop it from going to the fine leg fence.
Fuller on off, Harris pushes it towards cover and rotates strike.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
FOUR! On the pads of Marnus, he flicks it between mid-wicket and square leg as he finds the gap and the ball races to the fence. Good over for the Aussies this.
On the pads of Harris to start off with, he pushes it towards the man at mid-wicket.
Another one fuller and on the pads, Harris looks to push this towards mid on but gets the inner half of his bat on it. The ball rolls towards square leg and the batters take a couple.
Length ball outside off by Broad, Harris leaves it alone.
Again outside off, Harris lets it through to Bairstow.
On the pads of Harris, he flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.

OUT! LBW! The review is retained but Australia lose their second wicket in the form of Marcus Harris. This was pitched on a length around the fourth stump line by Broad, he gets it to angle into the southpaw. Harris looks to come on the front foot and defend it but misses the ball to get hit high on the pad. The English players appeal and the umpire raises his finger after thinking for a long time. Harris is not totally convinced that this would hit the stumps. He has a chat with Labuschagne at the non-striker's end and goes for the review at the last second. Ultra Edge comes in and shows no edge on that. Ball Tracker comes in now, pitching outside off, impact in line and wickets CLIPPING! It is just touching the top of middle and leg poles and thus it is Umpire's call. Australia in a spot of bother now.
A length ball, outside off, Labuschagne is solid in defense.
Landed outside off, Marnus looks to defend but is squared up. The ball squirts off the outside edge behind point and the batsmen take a single. Now, to the contest. The real contest.
Outside off, not a bouncer, but on a length, left alone.
Perfect line and length, just around off, Smith gets a long way across his stumps and defends.
There comes the first bouncer! Easily passing over the batsman's head. Smith ducks under it and the crowd cheers! More of that, they want, don't they?
A length ball around off, solidly defended.

Woah! Some football out in the middle by Labuschagne. This is a length ball on the off pole line. He blocks it out onto the pitch. The ball is rolling behind and Marnus is maybe a bit worried that it would go onto the stumps. So he literally kicks the ball towards the man at point.
Outside off, left alone by Labuschagne.
Beaten! Beauty by Broad this. Length ball outside off, Marnus goes for the drive and misses as the ball has some extra bounce on it. It goes past the edge and Broad is all smiles out there.

On the pads of Labuschagne this time, he works it towards short leg and takes a step forward. Buttler is alert and has a shy at the stumps and hits but Marnus is well in by that time. Action all around!
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, left alone by Labuschagne. Another maiden for Broad.
FOUR! SUBLIME! Half volley outside off, Smith leans and drives it through the covers. No one moves.
Length ball coming into Smith, he hops and looks to flick but the ball comes back in sharply. It hits Smith on the thigh pads and the ball rolls towards point as the batters take a leg bye.

Left alone by Labuschagne but mightily close to the stumps. Marnus living dangerously here against Archer as this misses the wicket by a whisker. Although he is hit on the thigh pad as the ball goes to Bairstow.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Length ball around middle and off, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
Bouncer on the leg pole line, Labuschagne ducks under it and the ball goes through to Bairstow.
Length ball outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
This is on a good length on middle, Marnus defends it towards the man at mid on.
On the pads of Labuschagne, he flicks it gently towards fine leg and takes a single. Maybe a chance of a second but they opt against it.

Good fielding by Leach on the ropes as he saves a run for his side. On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards square leg and the ball is going at a great pace. Leach from fine leg runs to his left, put in a dive and stops the ball from crossing the fence. The batters take three in the meanwhile.
Length ball on middle and off, Labuschagne blocks it out off the back foot.
Way outside off this time, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Starts off with a ball on middle and leg, Smith pushes it towards the man at short mid-wicket.
This one is on the off pole line, it pitches and straightens. Smith guides it towards cover and takes a single.
Length ball on middle and leg, it is going down the leg side after pitching. Marnus tries to flick it but misses and the ball goes off his thigh pad towards fine leg and the batters take a leg bye.
Length ball outside off to Smith. He leaves it alone.
Outside off again to Smith, he again lets it through to Bairstow.
Bouncer on the last ball, Smith does well to duck under it at the last moment.
Full ball on off, Labuschagne blocks it back towards the bowler.
Another one on off, Labuschagne pushes it towards mid off.

FOUR! Beautiful shot! First half volley of the day by England and just a push by Labuschagne on this. Full ball on middle and leg, Labuschagne leans on his front foot and pushes it through mid on for a boundary. The pace of the outfield and the slope of the ground also helped a bit in taking the ball towards the fence.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Outside off again, Marnus leaves it alone.

FOUR! Just a flick and boom, a boundary! Broad bowls this full and on the pads of Marnus, he flicks it with class towards mid-wicket, in the gap and the ball races towards the fence. Good over for the Aussies this. 8 off it.
A length ball outside off, Smith gets across and defends it towards cover.
Outside off, left alone.
A bouncer, around off, Smith ducks awkwardly but the extra height on that one enables him to get away with that.
FOUR! SWEET! Overpitched, outside off, Smith leans and drives it through the covers. Jofra Archer ambles after it from cover but never gets close to the ball.
FOUR! Cracking shot. Short and outside off, Smith rocks back and pulls it through mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Around off, solidly defended from the crease.
FOUR! Bad ball. Short and outside off, Labuschagne goes back and punches it behind point. The ball races away.
FOUR! Short again, outside off once more, Marnus cuts it behind point again and beats backward point.
Outside off, another long hop, this is punched through point. Would have been a hat-trick of boundaries but after the previous two gifts, Root has insurance at sweeper cover. Just a single.
Full and around off, just defended back to the bowler.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, in that corridor of go-for-the-drive, Labuschagne looks to drive but misses.

Hmmm... top edge now. Looks like Marnus is running out of patience. After playing a loose shot on the previous ball, he goes for the pull on this one. Gets a top edge which lobs in the air but does not carry to long leg. A single taken.
FOUR! A short ball, down the leg side, Smith pulls it with total control through fine leg to find the fence.
Down the leg side, helped fine for a single.

UMPIRE'S CALL! Clipping the leg stump and Labuschagne will stay. Banana swing. Gosh. How do you play that? Full and outside off, Labuschagne looks to let it go initially, but then tries to play it, due to the late swing. He is hit on the pads, caught between playing and leaving. England appeal but Stokes immediately signals going down the leg side. Root comes forward for a chat with his champion who is on his haunches in frustration but eventually takes the review. Here comes Ball Tracker. Clipping the leg stump! Review retained. Erasmus smiles. Looked to be going down leg to the naked eye but had Erasmus given it out, Labuschagne would have been out of here.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Action replay of the previous delivery.
Similar ball, this time Smith lunges to block.
Outside off, pushed back once more.
Full and outside off, plenty of flight, driven straight to cover.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Well outside off, left alone.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Full and outside off, watchfully blocked out.
Well outside off, let through.
A short ball, pulled through square leg for a single.
A length ball around off, Smith gets squared up as the ball moves away. Takes the outside edge, past third slip, towards third man. A couple of runs taken.
Tossed up outside off, Labuschagne lunges and works it towards short mid-wicket.
Pushed through cover for a quick single.
Outside off, punched through cover-point for a run.

Ooohhh.. almost superman-like from Ben Stokes! Full and around off, Marnus lunges to flick but the ball spins away and takes the leading edge. Because the batsman is looking to go leg side, Stokes at first slip takes an initial step to his left. But the ball goes to his right and he flings himself but cannot get there. Two runs down to third man. 50-RUN STAND IS UP between these two, in just 70 balls.
Around off, solidly defended.

Beauty! Superb bowling. This is just Day 1, yet he is getting good purchase. Full and outside off, ML leans to block but the ball whizzes past the outside edge. Does not miss off stump by much either.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Down the leg side, helped through fine leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
One more leave outside off.
Landed outside off, watchfully pushed towards cover.
Full and around off, blocked back to the bowler.
Around off, well blocked out.
Goes back, converts the full ball into a length one, which is normally short for a spinner and works it through square leg for a single.
Picks this from the off stump and punches it towards cover.
Full and around middle, Labuschagne lunges and pushes it towards mid on.
Very full, Marnus keeps it out.
Full and straight, targetting those pads, but Smith, as he so often does, gets his bat in the way, whipping this through square leg for a single.
Around middle and off, Labuschagne flicks it through square leg, calls for two as he sees fine leg and mid-wicket pretty deep. Gets two comfortably.
Outside off, on a length, shouldered arms to.
Another leave outside off. This one was a wider ball and Labuschagne does a Smith, swishing his bat away from the line.
Around off, watchfully pushed towards mid on.

SMITH WOULD HAVE BEEN RUN OUT HAD THE BALL HIT THE STUMPS! Full and around off, Labuschagne drives it straight back. Overton sticks out his right leg and almost does two things at one time - Injure himself and run Smith out behind him. He is on the ground but the ball just misses the stumps. The batsmen now take two. Replays show that Smith's bat was in the air when the ball went past the sticks.
Landed outside off, Smith lunges and blocks it out.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler once again.
Tossed up outside off, Steven stays leg side of the ball and drives it past short extra cover, wide of mid off. A single taken.
Down the leg side, helped through square leg for a couple.
Full and around middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a run.
Around middle, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! AMAZING! Full and outside off, Labuschagne leans and drives it through cover, past the fielder diving to his left, finding the ropes behind.
Around off, solidly defended.

That is a jaffa. Overton hits the deck hard, bowling it on a length and generates extra bounce. The ball whizzes past the outside edge and Bairstow appeals but he does not get enough support from the slip cordon. They join in late and on seeing that, Overton appeals as well. The umpire says no. Nothing on the Ultra Edge.
Around off, solidly defended.

That seemed to be deliberate from Overton. Labuschagne does get a long way across his stumps and Chris targets the leg stump, but bowls it slightly wide. Marnus attempts to flick but misses. Another half-shout, this time from the slips. Nothing from Bairstow or Overton.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Around middle, pushed towards cover.
Full and just around off, watchfully defended in front of silly point.
Full and around off, Smith pushes it towards long on. Labuschagne wants a single but he is sent back as short mid-wicket dives to his left.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and around off, watchfully kept out.
FOUR! Nicely timed. Full and outside off, Labuschagne leans and drives it behind point. The ball beats the diving gully fielder and races to the fence. Moves to 49.
Around off, pushed to the off side.
A good thinking bouncer, down the leg side, Marnus is surprised and ducks awkwardly at the last moment.
A length ball outside off, ML thinks about playing at it but withdraws his bat at the last moment. Almost has a Warneresque dismissal.
Full and around off, watchfully pushed towards mid on.
Down the leg side, Marnus misses his flick. LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Good length delivery outside off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around middle, Smith looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes through point. A single taken.
A bouncer outside off, Labuschagne sways away from the line.
Full and outside off, swinging away, Labuschagne looks to defend but gets a thick leading edge. The ball goes behind and third slip dives to his right and stops it.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Around middle, flicked through square leg for a single. 100 UP FOR AUSTRALIA.
Full and outside off, Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball moves away and beats the outside edge. The ball does not carry to Jonny Bairstow.
Landed outside off, watchfully defended.

HALF CENTURY FOR LABUSCHAGNE. His 5th in Tests, 4th in this series itself. A length ball, down the leg side, Marnus gets across and works it through mid-wicket for a single. The job is not yet done though.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, watchfully pushed back.
Full and down the leg side, flicked towards long leg for a single.
Around off, Smith gets across and defends.
A harmless bouncer down the leg side, Steven ducks under it.
Another bouncer, around off, another duck.
A length ball, around middle, Smith gets back and across and tucks it through square leg. A quick single pinched.
Around off, tucked straight to short leg.
FOUR! AWESOME! Great shot. Loosener from Broad and Smith does not miss out. Overpitched, around off, Steven gets across and drives it powerfully down the ground through mid on.
Around off, SS gets across and bunts it out.

Not a bad ball at all from Broad. He slows down his pace a touch and targets the middle stump. Smith is early into position and flicks this from middle stump, through mid-wicket. Jofra Archer lumbers after it but Jos Buttler races to his left at deep mid-wicket. Dives full stretch to parry the ball to Archer. Three runs taken.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR LEG BYES! Was it a case for LBW? Broad and Root have a thought but do not go for the review. A length ball, around middle, Labuschagne gets across to flick but misses. The ball goes off his pads past the diving Bairstow, to his left and races to the fine leg fence. Ball Tracker shows it to be missing leg stump.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground. 11 from the over.
A length ball outside off, solidly defended towards cover.
FOUR! SMOKED! Ordinary ball. Short and outside off, Smith arches back and flays it behind point for a boundary! The stand is worth 90 from 140 balls. Smith moves to 42 from 63 with his 6th boundary.
Full and straight, watchfully defended.
A bouncer, outside off, Steven sways away from the line.
A length ball, outside off, SS gets across, blocks and then swishes his bat through thin air.
A bouncer, down the leg side, ducked under.
Around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball, outside off, another one let through.
Full and down the leg side, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and straight, Smith gets across and flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
A short ball, around middle, pulled behind square leg for a couple.
Around off, Smith gets across and defends.
Outside off, left alone.
A bouncer, around off, ducked under.
Full and straight, SS blocks it out watchfully.
Another solid defense.
A length ball outside off, solidly defended.
Around off, pushed back down the ground.
Around off again, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, left alone.
A length ball, down the leg side, helped towards fine leg for a single.
A length ball, wide outside off, Smith shoulders arms.
A length ball outside off, Labuschagne taps it towards point, looks up at Smith and takes off for a quick single.
A short ball, outside off, pulled through mid-wicket for a run.
A length ball outside off, Marnus hops across and defends.
Full and wide outside off, left alone.
A short ball, down the leg side, ML takes his gloves out of the way as he lets it pass.
Around off, Labuschagne tucks it behind square leg. England have a leg gully in place but it escapes him. A single taken.
Full and straight, watchfully defended.
FOUR! 100-RUN STAND IS UP! Full and outside off, Labuschagne looks to drive but the ball goes off the outside edge past third slip towards the third man fence. Good fight.
Outside off, solidly defended.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Outside off, punched wide of cover for a quick single. Stokes has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Labuschagne had to run around the bowler and had to stretch. Would have been touch and go.

Huge, huge LBW shout! No, says the umpire. A length ball, outside off, Smith gets across and shoulders arms. Overton roars out an appeal but when the umpire turns it down, he himself tells Root that it was probably not coming back in that much.
Outside off, pushed through the covers for a single.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Gets across and works it through square leg for a run.
Landed outside off, left alone.
A length ball, down the leg side, nudged towards fine leg for one.
Around off, solidly defended towards mid on.

Another LBW shout. Is it too high? Overton seems to indicate that. A length ball, outside off, Labuschagne looks to defend but misses and is hit on the pads. The bowler initially appeals but umpire Erasmus shakes his head. Overton then indicates to Root that it might be too high. Ball Tracker shows the impact to be umpire's call but the ball would have gone over.
Around off, solidly defended to the off side.
A good length delivery around off, watchfully blocked out.
Full and around off, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
Similar ball, same shot, same region, same result.
FOUR! Late cut! Risky but well played. A length ball outside off, Labuschagne steers it with an open bat-face and guides it behind gully to third man! The stand moves to 110 now.

FOUR! HALF CENTURY FOR SMITH NOW! 26th in Tests, 8th in the Ashes. Gets there in bizarre fashion. Full and miles outside off, Smith reaches out, slips and almost dives to get bat to ball. Manages to get it through cover but was there any need to go after that? He could have so easily nicked it behind or handed a catch to cover-point. Remember Ben Stokes' dismissal in the first innings of the previous Test? Anyways, another terrific innings.
Around off, nudged through square leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
One more leave outside off.
A hat-trick of leaves now.
Around middle and off, clipped through mid-wicket for a run.
Around off, watchfully defended.

OUT! BOWLED! A jaffa to break a terrific stand. We felt someone had to do something special to break this partnership and Overton has done it. This is so, so similar to his first Test wicket in Adelaide. That time, it was Smith. This time, it is Labuschagne. Nothing much either batsman could have done on either occasion. A length ball, outside off, Labuschagne looks to defend, thinking he has covered the line but the ball seams back in, goes between bat and pad and hits the top of off stump! End of a terrific knock from Labuschagne. The 116-run stand is broken at last.
Outside off, Head pushes at it but the ball moves away and beats the outside edge.
FOUR! Wrong line. Overpitched outside leg, Head flicks it through square leg and gets off the mark.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
A length ball, outside off, Travis plays inside the line and gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes past third slip and three runs are taken.
Outside off, a play and a miss.
Outside off, steered through point for three more.
Full and outside off, driven back to the bowler.
A bouncer, outside off, Smith ducks under it.
A short ball, around off, Steven gets inside the line and pulls it through square leg for one.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
A length ball, down the leg side, helped through square leg for a couple.
Another length ball, outside off, Smith hops and defends.
Full and outside off, Steven takes his bat away from the line.
A length ball, a bit too straight, SS just places it behind square on the leg side and finds the gap. Mid-wicket and fine leg intersect in the deep but by then, three runs have been taken.
Full and straight, worked towards square leg.
Drifting in from around the wicket to the left-hander, helped through square leg but straight to the fielder.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to mid off.
A short ball, outside off, Smith hops and plays it nicely through third slip. Rory Burns dives to his right and gets some pace off the ball but hurts his hand in the process. A single taken.

PITCHED OUTSIDE LEG! End of story. A yorker, by Stokes, Head looks to flick but loses his balance and slips. Is hit on the left boot and Stokes appeals but umpire Kumar Dharmasena is not impressed. Root has a chat with his bowler and goes for the review. Ball Tracker confirms that a review is lost for England. Superb decision by umpire Dharmasena. Looked very close to the naked eye. Not the umpire of the year without a reason!
Outside off, on a length, Travis plays inside the line, feeling for it and misses.

FOUR! JUST OVER! That is why that man has been placed there. Full and down the leg side, Head flicks it and it looks to be a very good shot. Till Jos Buttler flies across to his left at squarish mid-wicket. But the ball flies over him to the fence at mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Landed outside off, Smith dabs it straight to point.
Banged in short, pulled through mid-wicket for a single. Smith moves to 60 now.
Full and outside off, Head looks to drive, without moving his feet and misses.
FOUR! Wrong line and punished. A length ball, down the leg side, Head tucks it through square leg. Plenty of free real estate there.
Comes around the wicket, bowls it on a length outside off, Travis looks to defend but then tries to take the bat away. The ball goes off the toe end towards third slip.
Outside off, left alone. TEA ON DAY 1!
First ball of the day, the ball has found the edge of Smith's bat.
Length ball outside off, Smith tries to push this one towards the off side but is beaten.
Length ball on off again, Smith pushes this one off the back foot back towards the bowler.
Bouncer just outside off, Smith ducks under it and lets it through to Bairstow.
Good length ball this time, mixing it up. Smith comes onto the front foot and pushes it back towards Broad.
Australia are underway on Day 2. This is a length ball on the pads, Smith flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Beaten! Good ball to start off Day 2 for Archer. He pitches this on a length just outside off and gets it to move away from Smith. He tries to defend it but does so inside the line and is beaten.
FOUR! Great reply by Smith. This is fuller and outside off, Smith pushes this towards cover even as his bottom hand comes off the bat. But the ball races to the fence. First boundary of the day!

DROPPED AND FOUR! Almost into the hands of Archer. A low full toss by Archer on middle, Smith pushes it back towards him uppishly. Archer gets his right hand's fingertips to it but the ball goes through his hand and straight down the ground towards the long off fence.

Inside edge and almost chopped on. Length ball just outside off, Smith looks to push it towards the off side but gets the inside half of his bat on it and the ball rolls past the stumps towards fine leg as the batters take one.
On the pads, Head flicks it towards the leg side.
Beaten again! Outside off, Head looks to push at this one but is beaten by the away movement.
Short and on the body. Smith pulls but does not time it well and the ball goes on the bounce to backward square leg.
On a length and outside off, Smith leaves it with his unique left alone style.
Short and down the leg side, Smith ducks under it comfortably.
Length and on middle, Smith defends it back to the bowler.
Another bouncer and Smith ducks under it easily.
Short of good length on middle and leg, Smith flicks it off his back foot to mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball just outside off, nips back in to Smith. He tries to block it out but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Bouncer by Archer, to Smith. This is on the leg pole line, Smith ducks out of the way at the last moment.
Short of a length ball outside off, Smith looks to push it towards the off side but the ball hits his gloves and goes to point.
Outside off, left alone by Smith.
Length ball on middle and leg, Smith pushes it towards mid on off the back foot.
Bouncer off the last ball. On the off pole line, Smith does well to sway away from it.
Broad comes around the wicket, bowls a length ball outside off. Head pushes out off the back foot.

On the pads of Head there, he flicks it towards backward square leg. Jack Leach runs to his right from fine leg and the batters take one. There was a second on offer but Head takes a slow start. Also, he has to run around the bowler, so when he turns for the second, he realizes that he cannot make it to the striker's end in time. So he sends Smith back. Michael Atherton on air informs that Jack Leach is a left-hand batsman, left-arm bowler but he throws with his right hand. Interesting.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.

OUT! LBW! Travis Head is outta here and the hosts get their first breakthrough of the day. Broad is the man again. He bowls this on a length outside off, it comes in with the angle. Head looks to block it out but misses as the ball hits him on the knee roll. The English players appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Smith and Head mull over taking the review but eventually decide against it. Replays roll in and Ball Tracker shows it to be clipping leg.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards fine leg and the batters take one. Wade is off the mark.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Bouncer down the leg side, Wade ducks under it and lets the ball through.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards the leg side.
Length ball outside off, Wade pushes this towards cover off the back foot.
Archer bangs this one short of a length, the ball comes in with the angle. Wade looks to sway away from it but is hit on the forearm. He looks in some pain here.

Edged and just short of Joe Root at first slip! Length ball outside off, Wade looks to push this one towards the off side but he gets a thick edge on it. The ball falls short of Root and goes through the slip cordon. The skipper himself mops it up running back. Two runs taken. For a second, Roy perhaps thought about going for the catch but then bailed out. Not sure he might have got to it either.
Short of a length ball, Smith pulls this one towards square leg and takes one.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards the man at fine leg.

Beaten! Jaffa by Broad! This one is on a length and just outside off, it pitches and then leaves the batsman. Wade goes for the block but is beaten by the movement on it. Misses the outside edge by a whisker.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Bouncer to Smith off the last ball off the over. He ducks under it.
Length ball outside off, Wade pushes it off the back foot towards the point region and takes a single.
Length ball outside off, this time to Smith, he pushes it towards the man at cover off the back foot.
Another bumper to Smith by Archer. Smith does well to duck under it.
FOUR! Great shot by Smith! This is a length ball outside off, Smith just guides it towards the empty third man region and the ball races towards the fence.
Archer looks fired up now. Goes above the 90 mph mark. A bumper on middle and off, Smith is just consistently evading them.
Another bouncer to end the over. Smith is patient and he lets it through to Bairstow. Archer getting itchy here.
Length ball just outside off, Wade shuffles onto his back foot and pushes this towards point where they take a quick single.
This is on the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards Stokes at backward square leg.

JUST WIDE! Almost the plan works. Decent stuff from Broad. This time on a length and on middle, Smith pulls this one uppishly towards fine leg. Now, Ben Stokes has been stationed at backward square leg, exactly for that catch off the pull shot. But the ball just evades him and goes to long leg. A single taken.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Bouncer down the leg side, Smith evades it.
Length ball way outside off, Smith leaves it alone in his own typical fashion.
Good length ball on off, coming back in to Wade. He blocks it out.
Length ball on off, pushed out by Wade.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Matthew.
Another length ball outside off, Wade opens the face of his bat and guides it towards the third slip fielder.
Way down the leg side, Wade leaves it alone.
Another one on the leg side, Wade looks to flick this one but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters take a leg bye.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Wade.
Fullish ball outside off, Wade gets on the front foot and pushes it towards cover as the batters take a couple.
Another length ball outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Full by Broad, just outside off, Wade pushes it down the ground. Broad gets down in an attempt to gather the ball but he parries it towards mid off.
Length ball outside off, Wade guides this off the back foot towards the slip cordon. He thinks that there is a single on there but Smith denies it.
Outside off, left alone by Wade.
Length ball outside off by Archer, he pushes it back towards mid on.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a quick single.
FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Wade just opens the face of the bat and guides this one between point and gully as the ball races towards the third man fence.
Length ball on middle and off, Wade defends it from within the crease towards mid off.
NO BALL! Archer oversteps as he looks to go for the bouncer this time. Wade ducks and lets that one through to Bairstow.

Length ball outside off, Wade goes for the pull but misses it. England put in a stifled appeal for a caught behind but nothing from the umpire. Root now comes towards his bowler and has a chat regarding the review but eventually does not take it. Here comes Ultra Edge. Nothing on it when the ball passes the bat.
Down the leg side, Wade goes for the flick but misses. The ball kisses his pads and goes towards the fine leg boundary.
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman. The batsmen have run through for a single.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it off his pad towards short leg.

Tossed up on middle and off, Wade goes for the paddle but Stokes from first slip runs to his right, pre-meditating it and stops the ball from going towards the fine leg fence. An excellent effort from him as the crowd applauds.
Tossed up ball on middle and off, Wade pushes this one onto the ground.
FOUR! Flighted by Leach on the pads of Wade, he comes down the track and flicks it towards mid-wicket as the ball races to the fence.
Full and floated outside off, Wade pushes this off the front foot towards mid off.
Bouncer to start off by Overton on the leg pole line. Smith ducks under it.
Another bouncer by Overton, Steven again ducks under it.
On the pads of Smith this time, he flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Length ball outside off, Wade defends it off the back foot.
Another length ball outside off, Wade pushes this one towards mid off.
Outside off, Wade pushes this one towards the off side.
Flat on off pole, a bit of turn. Smith blocks it out.

Confusion out in the middle and Smith survives! This is floated on the leg side, Smith tucks it towards square leg and goes for the quick single. Wade though does not respond and Smith is left high and dry. He scampers back as Bairstow goes for the direct hit towards the keeper's end but misses. Ben Stokes comes to the stumps at the striker's end but he overruns a bit. He then lets the throw through because it comes in very fast but Smith was in due to the dive.
FOUR! Whipped and whipped well. This is floated on the pads again, Smith just comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flat on off, the ball pitches and turns. Smith looks to block off the back foot but is beaten. He then indicates towards his partner that he is shocked by that turn.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated outside off, Smith drives this superbly towards cover and takes a single.
Length ball outside off, Smith pushes this towards point off the back foot.
On the middle pole line, Smith looks to pull this one but misses to get hit on the hips. The ball rolls towards leg gully and the batters take a leg bye.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards the leg side.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fuller and on the off side, Wade pushes this towards mid off.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards the leg side.
Tossed up on the pads, Smith flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple.
Floated outside off by Leach, Smith plays it onto the ground.
On the pads of Smith again, he flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

OUT! CAUGHT! Wade is out of here and Australia are five down now! Leach tosses this one just outside off, Wade comes down the track and looks to heave this one over mid-wicket. However, he is nowhere near the pitch of the ball. Hence, he gets a top edge as the ball skies towards mid on. Joe Root over there, staggers, stutters and even trembles a bit but eventually takes the catch. The 41-run partnership is broken and Wade departs for just 16.
Paine drives this through the covers by the batsman.
Bouncer to start off with by Overton, Smith ducks under it.
Another bouncer, Smith pulls this one onto the ground and the ball goes towards backward square leg as the batters take one.
Length ball outside off, Paine defends this off the back foot by the batsman.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Another short ball, Paine goes for the pull and takes a single as the ball goes towards square leg.
Outside off, Smith opens the face of the bat and guides it towards third man for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, Smith cuts it towards point but uppishly. However, luckily for him, the ball lands short of the man at short third man.
Full and outside off, Smith comes down the track to defend but the ball goes off his pads past silly point towards cover.
Smith has played it to the point region and the batters have run through for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Length ball outside off, Paine cuts it towards point and takes a single.
Overton bowls a bouncer and Paine ducks under it.
This is a half-bumper, actually not all that short. However, Paine ducks under it and it just goes above his elbow down the leg side. Guess he did not pick the length.
Another bouncer, this time on the leg pole line, Paine is months early into the duck.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Short again by Overton, Paine pulls this one towards fine leg and takes a single.
On the pads of Smith this time, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Full and floated outside off, pushed towards mid off by the batsman.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Full and floated on the pads, Paine flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Driven through mid off by the batsman.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full and floated on off, blocked out by Paine.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
On the pads of Paine, he flicks it towards the leg side.
Outside off, Paine initially looks to play at it but then bails out at the last moment.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Full and outside off, Paine blocks it onto the ground.
Length ball outside off, Paine defends the ball off the back foot.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards short fine leg and takes a single.
This time on middle and leg, Paine pushes this towards mid-wicket for a run.
Shorter and outside off, Smith cuts this towards cover and takes a single.
Full and floated on off, blocked out by Paine.
Outside off, left alone by Paine.
Floated outside off, Paine blocks it onto the ground.
WIDE! Bouncer down the leg side but too high by Overton. Wide signalled.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards backward square leg. Smith moves onto 99.
Short again by Overton, Paine pulls it away towards square leg and gives the strike to Smith.

CENTURY FOR STEVEN SMITH! 26th Test Hundred and 3rd in this year's Ashes for the no.1 Test batsman in the world. This is on the pads of Smith and he flicks it towards square leg. Ben Stokes stationed at square leg dives to his left but cannot stop the ball. It goes past him and the man from short mid-wicket rushes after it. By that time, two runs are taken. Smith takes his helmet off and soaks in the applause from the dressing room. The 1940s saw the dawn of THAT Don. The 2000s are seeing the dawn of THIS Don. Take a bow, Mr. rightly-called Precocious.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Length ball around off, Smith pushes this towards mid on.
Outside off, left alone by Smith.
Full and floated outside off, blocked out.
Shortish this time on off, Paine blocks it out off the back foot.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Excellent finding of the gap! Full and outside off, Paine comes forward and drives. Silly point jumps and the ball goes through his legs. Short extra cover gets across but cannot put in a dive. Joe Root does so, from mid off but his dive cannot take him near to the ball. It scoots through and the ball races to the fence.
Full and way outside off by Leach, pushed towards cover.

Great effort from Roy as he saves four runs for his side. This is full and floated outside off, Paine drives this one powerfully towards cover again. Jason Roy there, dives to his left and pulls off a great stop. He parries it towards point where the fielder mops it up. Roy takes ages to get up and looks like he has hurt his fingers. LUNCH ON DAY 2!
A length ball, around middle, Smith tucks this through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.

EDGED, DROPPED! Gosh. That was a sitter. Would have been the perfect start for England after the break. Full and outside off, Paine looks to drive but sans any footwork. The ball takes a thick outside edge and flies straight to Jason Roy at second slip, but he shells it. Tries to take it in the second attempt but cannot hang on.
Outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, driven past silly point to short extra cover.
Tossed up outside off, Smith comes down the track and defends.
Full and wide outside off, driven through the covers for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated around off, Paine comes forward and smothers the spin.
Around off, solidly kept out.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! Another back foot drive! How does he manage those? A length ball outside off, Smith goes back and punch-drives it through the covers. 250 UP FOR AUSTRALIA.
Around off, Steven gets across and nudges it through square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, Paine lets that go.
That is another peach. Broad lands it on a length, outside off, Tim looks to defend but then gets squared up. The ball moves away at the last moment and beats the outside edge.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.

IN THE AIR... SAFE! Wow. Smith and luck. Are they synonyms? Unbelievable. Flighted outside off, Smith comes down the track to have a heave but is not to the pitch of the ball at all. On top of that, Leach slows that one. The cherry takes the top edge and goes towards cover. Jason Roy runs back from short extra cover while Craig Overton comes running in from sweeper. But luckily for Smith, the ball lands in between! A single taken.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Paine rocks back and punches it through the covers!
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! BEAUTY! Loosener from Stokes, a gentle half volley outside off but even that has to be put away. Paine drives it straight back down the ground and beats wide mid on.
Around middle, worked through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Another bad ball. Short and down the leg side, Smith hooks it towards fine leg!

FOUR! How do you play that? Unbelievable from the 'I-make-them-look-believable' Smith. Outside off, on a length, Smith waits and waits and at the last moment, guides it between the second slip fielder and gully to third man!
NO BALL. Stokes oversteps now. Bowls this on a length outside off, Steven pushes it towards cover.
That is a peach. A length ball outside off, SS looks to flay that through the line but misses.
Around middle, worked through mid-wicket for a single. 15 from the over, Stokes' figures read 9-0-51-0!

Edged and taken! But Leach has overstepped! Wow. Seems like Steven Smith has taken some tuition classes to explain the synonym to luck to everyone. More and more luck for the legend. Unbelievable. A lovely delivery to start, flighted outside off, Smith looks to drive but the ball hits something. Yes, something. And then turns. The ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to Ben Stokes at first slip. Smith walks back but umpire Dharmasena wants a second look upstairs for the no ball. Here come the replays. The foot has landed outside the crease with the heel in the air, but on the line! England drop their heads down immediately on looking at the giant screen but Root gathers his team together and calms his players down. Very, very good job done.
Outside off, left alone.
Around off, clipped straight to short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, Smith comes down the track and blocks.
Eases this through the covers for a single.
Full and outside off, driven through mid off for a quick single.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. One run added to the total.
Full and outside off, solidly defended.

Oopss... a length ball outside off, Steven looks to defend but the ball hits the toe end of the bat and goes behind. Smith immediately rushes back and then hits the ball away. Jonny Bairstow is not happy with that as he was coming in to collect.
Around middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
NO BALL. Another overstepping from Stokes. Full and outside off, Paine pushes this through the covers and gets a quick single.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! When you are on 121, this is a gift. A full toss outside off, Smith leans and drives it through the covers.
Full and outside off, Paine drives it towards cover and sets off for a quick single. Joe Root rushes across and has a shy at the bowler's end, hitting the stumps, but his counterpart is well in.

IN THE AIR... SAFE! Another moment of luck for Smith. Full and outside off, Steven comes down the track and drives it hard towards silly point. It hits his pads and then lobs towards the bowler. Leach gets across to his left but the ball evades him!
Comes down the track and looks to defend but misses and is hit on the groin.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Around off, watchfully blocked out.
Full and around off, watchfully kept out.
Full and around off, Paine defends it watchfully.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Floated outside off, Tim gets his bat down to defend.
Outside off, driven straight to cover.
Short and outside off, cut straight to short third man.
On a length outside off, punched towards cover for a single.
Full and outside off, watchfully blocked out.
Short and outside off, cut through the covers for a run.
Floated outside off, watchfully blocked out.
Full and outside off, pushed towards the off side.
Around middle, flicked through mid-wicket for one.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Full and around middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and around middle, Paine looks to flick but the ball goes off the inner half of his bat towards short leg.
Around middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a run.
On middle and off, Smith swipes it towards short mid-wicket.
On middle and off, clipped through mid-wicket for one.
A length ball around off, watchfully defended.
Works it through mid-wicket for a single.
A bouncer on middle, Paine ducks.
FOUR! Cracking shot. Short and wide outside off, Paine cuts it through point for a boundary! The stand moves to 72 from 119 balls.
A length ball outside off, Paine looks to defend but then wants to take his bat away. The ball goes off the bottom edge towards gully.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Around off, solidly defended.
Around off, clipped through mid-wicket for a single.
Around off again, solidly blocked out.
A bouncer on middle, Tim ducks under it hurriedly.
Another bouncer, this time with lesser pace, ducked under again.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Comes from around the wicket, targets the stumps, but Smith flicks the full ball through square leg for a couple.
That was a jaffa. To a left-hander. Broad strays one down the leg side, Smith gets across and looks to flick but the ball swings away and beats his bat. Would have got a southpaw nicking behind.
FOUR! Stand and deliver. Full and wide outside off, Smith leans and eases this through the covers. 300 UP FOR AUSTRALIA with that.
Full and outside off, driven through the covers for a single. The stand moves to 80 from 131 balls.
A short ball, around off, Paine swivels and pulls this through mid-wicket for a run.
Yorker outside off, watchfully dug out.
Full and down the leg side, Paine flicks it through square leg and returns for the second.
Around middle, clipped through mid-wicket for a single.
Around middle, clipped through mid-wicket for a run.
Very full, outside off, Paine looks to drive but mistimes it towards mid off.
A bouncer, around middle, Tim ducks.
A good length ball, around off, watchfully defended.
Down the leg side, Smith gets a long way across and then takes his bat away from the line.
A bouncer on middle, Steven ducks under it.
Full and down the leg side, SS misses his flick.
A jaffa again. Broad hits the length, landing it outside off, Smith looks to defend but is squared up. The ball moves away to beat the outside edge.
Edge this time, but not to hand! A length ball, in line of the stumps, Steven looks to defend but is squared up again. The ball goes off the outside edge, past third slip and he gets a couple.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot for a couple.
Full and outside off, Paine looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
FOUR! BRILLIANT! Pretty straight, full and outside off, a bit of width, Paine cashes in and drives it through the covers. The stand is worth 93 from 147 balls now.
Landed outside off, left alone.
A bouncer now, let through.
Full and down the leg side, flick shot missed.
A length ball, just around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, watchfully defended.
On a length outside off, coming in, Smith looks to defend but the ball shapes away late to beat the outside edge.
Landed outside off, on a length, Steven takes his bat away from the line.
One more leave outside off.
Ahhh... another one of those edges. Full and straight, Smith looks to defend but is squared up. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards third slip, but on the bounce.
Around middle, worked through mid-wicket for a run.
Landed outside off, Smith lets it through.
On a good length outside off, Steven shoulders arms.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
A length ball outside off, coming in, SS looks to flick but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.
On a good length outside off, let through again.
Full and outside off, let through once more.

A full ball wide outside off, Paine thinks to go after it but then lets it go as it is just too wide. The ball goes well outside the pitch and Bairstow has to dive to his right, to take it in front of first slip but no wide signalled.
A short ball, down the leg side, this is pulled down to long leg for a single.
Landed outside off, left alone.
On middle and leg, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Around middle and leg, flicked through fine leg for a run.
Landed outside off, left alone.
A short ball, down the leg side, Paine looks to pull but misses.
FOUR! CARESSED! Half volley outside off, Paine comes forward and drives it between cover and mid off. Stuart Broad gives it a good chase from mid off but the ball wins the race. 100-RUN STAND IS UP!
Landed outside off, left alone.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Full and outside off, swinging away, gentle pace, in the mid 80s, the skipper lets it go.
Full and around off, Smith works it wide of mid on for a single.
Around off, solidly defended towards cover.
FOUR! CLASSY! Half volley outside off, into the mid 80s is Stokes, Paine leans and drives it through the covers.

Excellent stop by Jofra Archer! Full and around off, the skipper drives it straight down the ground. Mid on and mid off give it a chase with Jofra Archer getting to the ball from the latter position. Puts in a dive and pulls the ball back in. Three runs taken.
A bouncer now, Steven ducks.
Full and outside off, Smith drives it through the covers for a single.
A length ball, down the leg side, Smith gets across and nudges it through square leg for a single.
Full and down the leg side, Paine misses his flick.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, let through.
Full and around off, Tim looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Landed outside off, let through to Bairstow once more.
Full and outside off, Smith gets across to defend but at the last moment, takes his bat out of the way.

150 UP FOR STEVEN SMITH! The machine goes on and on and on. A short ball, around middle, Smith drags this through mid-wicket and returns for the third. Raises his bat to the crowd. Does he look bored?
A bouncer, around middle, Paine ducks.
Another bouncer, the skipper ducks again. Second bouncer for the over signalled by umpire Kumar Dharmasena.
A short ball outside off, Tim pulls it straight to straightish mid on.

DROPPED! Another one goes down. It is Sam Curran, the substitute. A short ball, outside off, Paine pulls it or rather swats it towards mid on. It is straight to Curran, as on the previous ball and he gets down to his left to take the catch as well. But shells it. Paine smiles.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, Smith looks to defend but is squared up. The ball goes off the outside edge towards gully.
FOUR! Help yourself. Full and outside off, pretty wide, Smith leans and drives it through the covers.

Full and outside off, Steven looks to play the cover drive again but the ball hits the toe end of the bat and goes back to the bowler. Craig Overton looks to pick and have a shy at the striker's end but does not collect the ball.
On a length around off, solidly defended.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
A bouncer on middle, Paine ducks.
A short ball, outside off, the skipper stands tall and fends it towards point.

A sharp short ball, outside off, Tim takes his bat away from the line as he offers a leave. However, the ball keeps coming in and almost takes the outside edge. Jonny Bairstow collects and appeals but no one supports him. Nothing from the umpire.
A short ball, outside off, Tim pulls it away but Jos Buttler at short leg stops it nicely.
A bouncer again, TP ducks.
Another bouncer to end the over, Paine ducks again.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! CLASSY! Boundary number 18 for Smith. Another fine shot. Full and straight, Smith drives it straight back to where it came from. Through mid on and to the fence.
Easy-peasy. Full and around off, Steven works it wide of mid on for a couple. Moves to 161.
A bouncer around off, Steven sways away from the line, even though the ball goes past his face. The ball dips and barely carries to the keeper.
What was that? A short ball, outside off, SS looks to pull/hook and ends up swatting it. Gets a top edge which does not carry to long leg. A single taken.
Outside off, left alone.
A short ball outside off, Smith arches his back and guides it but finds Ben Stokes at gully.
FOUR! Off the glove. A short ball, down the leg side, Smith gets across to nudge and just gets it past a diving Jonny Bairstow to the fine leg fence.
Landed outside off, left alone.
A bouncer, around off, Steven ducks.
Around middle, worked straight to mid-wicket.
Another leave outside off to end the over.
Full and around off, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.

FIFTY FOR PAINE! After spending 17 balls on 49, Paine finally gets to the mark which has eluded him for the last 17 innings in Tests. Full and outside off, Paine reaches out and drives it through mid off. A single taken to finally raise his bat.
Around off, solidly defended.
Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on.
A length ball, in line of the stumps, worked through mid-wicket for a single.
Landed outside off, Tim shoulders arms and then pads it away.
IN THE AIR... JUST SHORT! A short ball outside off, Smith ramps it towards third man and almost finds the fielder. Joe Denly comes running in but cannot quite get to the ball. A single taken.
Outside off, left alone. The ball comes in and then hits Bairstow hard on the gloves, around the fingers. He winces in pain.
A bouncer around middle, Paine ducks.
Full and outside off, pushed through the covers for a couple.
Bouncer! The batsman ducks under the bouncer at the last moment.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Paine cuts it behind point and gets a boundary!
Full and around middle, Smith comes down the track and flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
On middle and leg, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, punched off the back foot by the batsman.
Full and around middle, Paine flicks it straight to short mid-wicket.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman. They pick up a single.
Full and around middle, worked towards short leg.
Full and around leg, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and down the leg side, Paine looks to flick but the ball goes off the inner half towards short fine leg. Paine wants a single but is then sent back.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Full and around middle, flicked away for a run.

FOUR! Oh dear. Loads of rubbish. A half-tracker, around middle, Smith heaves this wide of mid on and finds the fence as well. And with that STEVEN SMITH GOES PAST VIRAT KOHLI. He now has 6750 Test runs, as opposed to Kohli's 6749. Smith's average is 64.90, while VK's average is 53.14.
Full and around off, watchfully defended to end the session. TEA ON DAY 2!

OUT! Caught behind! A wicket on the very first ball after Tea! Will this spice England up? A length ball, outside off, Paine looks to defend but the ball straightens slightly to take a thin outside edge. Jonny Bairstow collects and appeals and Paine is on his bike. A dogged, watchful innings comes to an end and England break the 145-run stand at last.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended.
FOUR! Cummins is underway. Full and down the leg side, Patrick just tickles it towards the fine leg fence.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Outside off, played it straight to point.
Pushes this straight to point.
SIX! A full toss from Leach, Smith comes down the track and hammers it over mid-wicket. Just clears the ropes.
Outside off, punched off the back foot.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, punched through the covers for a single.
Full and outside off, driven back to the bowler.
Around off, watchfully defended.
WIDE! Full and outside the pitch. Smith gets across and then shoulders arms.
Landed outside off, let through.
Full and outside off again, let through.
Landed outside off, let through again.
An interesting leave this time. Steven lets it pass and then swats his bat through thin air.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
On middle and leg, helped through mid-wicket for a run.
Full and around off, Smith watchfully defends.
FOUR! Another freebie. A flighted ball, Smith dances down the track, converts  this into a full toss and whips this through mid-wicket.
Outside off, punched straight to point. Cummins rushes across for the single but then is sent back.
This time Smith gets a single, with a punch through point.
Full and around off, watchfully pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! Edged and taken. This is not a no ball. Nicely bowled. Flighted outside off, Cummins comes forward to defend but there is some extra bounce on this one. The ball hits the splice of the bat and goes towards first slip where Ben Stokes takes a sitter.
Outside off, Smith lets it go and then swishes at thin air.
A good length ball outside off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
A good length ball outside off, let through.
Around off, watchfully defended. It is a maiden which means Starc will be on strike in the next over!
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
On middle and off, watchfully defended.
Full and around middle, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
Around middle, watchfully pushed in front of short leg.
Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. He has seen this over off.
Good length delivery outside off, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, left alone again.
FOUR! Into the 190s! A short ball outside off, Smith gets across and drags this wide of mid on for a boundary!
Outside off, left alone,.
Full and outside off, Smith looks to drive this through the covers but gets it off the inner half back to the bowler.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
Full and around off, pushed towards long on for a single.
Outside off, short in length, punched through the covers for a run.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
On middle, flicked towards short leg.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Full and wide outside off, left alone.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump again.

Almost a replica of yesterday. Full and miles outside off, Smith throws his bat at it, reaching out but cannot get his willow to touch it. He slips later too. Yesterday, he reached his half century while playing that shot.
WIDE. Now, this is outside the pitch and umpire Erasmus shoulders arms.
Landed outside off, let through again.
Full and around off, Smith works it towards mid on, calls for a quick single but then changes his mind.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around middle, pushed towards long on for a single.
Landed around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
That is a beauty. Leach tosses this up slowly outside off, Steven lunges to defend but the ball pitches and then spins away past the outside edge.
Outside off, Steven looks to cut but misses.
Full and around off, watchfully pushed towards cover.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, Starc looks to drive but makes no feet movement. Is beaten comprehensively.

EDGED, BUT DOES NOT CARRY. Full and outside off, Starc looks to push but the ball nibbles away and takes the outside edge. Unfortunately it does not carry to second slip. Ben Stokes gets across and tries to catch but gets hit on the fingers.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
FOUR! CRISP! Full and straight, Starc drives this straight back as an arrow and hits the long on fence!
Outside off, left alone.
SIX! Moves to 197! Full and outside off, Smith comes down the track and lofts it over mid off. He seems to have got enough on it and clears long off! 400 UP FOR AUSTRALIA!
Full and around off, Smith looks to flick and run towards square leg but then changes his mind.
Full and outside off, Steven lunges and pushes it towards cover-point.
Outside off, dabbed past slip. However, backward point gets across and slides to his left, keeping the batsmen to a single.
Full and around off, whacked straight to mid on.
Pushes this back to the bowler.
Outside off, punched straight to cover.
Landed outside off, left alone. Pretty wide again.

Moves to 199. A length ball outside off, Smith gets across, waits for the ball to come to him and then dabs it late towards third man. He is cross with himself the moment he plays that shot. Perhaps he wanted to get it behind point and extremely fine of third man for at least a couple. Gets only a single.
A bouncer now, around middle, Starc ducks.
Full and around off, Mitchell looks to drive but misses.
Outside off, left alone this time.

Oopss... Starc is in trouble! Safe in the end. A length ball, around off, Smith got across and tucked it straight to square leg. Rory Burns picked it but Starc was halfway down the track, eager to give his former skipper the strike. He was sent back rightly and Rory missed his shy at the bowler's end.

THIRD TEST DOUBLE CENTURY FOR STEVEN SMITH! All his three have been against England. Full and around off, Smith gets across and nudges it behind square leg. He runs hard for the second and then raises his bat to the crowd in jubilation. The helmet is off and the smile is back. Declaration now?
Outside off, left alone with a swish of the bat.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, Steven plays inside the line and is beaten.
FOUR! Fine shot. Full and around middle, Smith drives this through mid on and finds the long on fence.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
A full toss, around middle, Starc heaves it through mid-wicket for a couple.

Full and outside off, Mitchell looks to drive but misses. The ball pitches on the rough, spins away and goes behind. Bairstow is unable to collect and the ball goes off his gloves to first slip where Ben Stokes is hit on the left shin. Hobbles in pain.
Outside off, MS plays inside the line and is beaten.
Outside off, dabbed straight to backward point.
The arm ball, Starc looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. There is an appeal from Bairstow but Root himself is not interested. Going down leg perhaps.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Gets across and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! That is a full toss, on the pads and Starc tickles it to the fine leg fence.
FOUR! SPANKED! Starc has got the license. Full and on middle, Starc hammers this straight back past the bowler through mid on!
FOUR! Hat-trick of boundaries! Starc is in the mood. Full and straight again, Starc bashes it over mid on!

FOUR! A bit streaky this time and Starc is having fun at Broad's cost. A length ball outside off, pretty wide, Starc throws his bat at it and gets a thick outside edge which flies behind point to the fence! 17 from the over.
Looks like the declaration is around the corner. Smith backs a long way to the leg side and then carves it over cover for a single.
Full and outside off, driven back to the bowler.
Outside off, punched towards cover for a run.
FOUR! Terrific shot. Full and down the leg side, Smith paddles this through fine leg and beats the man in the deep, to his right! 50-RUN STAND is up between these two as well!

OUT! Oh dear. What has happened? Is the press working? Stop it. Restart. Steven Smith has been dismissed. Yes, you read that right. Steven Smith has been dismissed. Copy that. Roger that. England could not find a way to get him out, so he himself has got out. Full and outside off, Smith looks to play the reverse sweep but finds Joe Denly at short third man. Interestingly, Root, who is an off spinner, tried the leg spin and voila, it worked! The best batsman of the opposition is gone at last. Just a paltry 211. All the England players rush across to congratulate the great man.
Played to the point region by the batsman. They pick up a single.
Down the leg side, Lyon looks to flick but misses.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

TOP EDGE, FOUR! A short ball, around middle, Lyon looks to pull but gets a top edge which sails over long leg! The fielder runs across to his left but cannot get there! The ball just bounces into the ropes.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Stunning shot. Outside off, Lyon punches it through the covers for a boundary!
Pushes this straight to point.
Full and around middle, Starc goes back to punch but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
SIX! TAKE THAT! Tossed up, outside off, Starc gets down and mows it over mid-wicket for half a dozen!

NOT OUT. There is glove involved. Full and around off, Starc got down and across to middle but missed and was hit on the pads. The ball rolled down to fine leg and Starc took a single but Bairstow was confidently appealing and suggested that Root should take the review. The skipper seemed disinterested but then took it. Ultra Edge detected glove when the ball went past the glove.
On middle and leg, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Another mow. Full and outside off, Starc gets down and swings this cleanly over mid-wicket. Stuart Broad at wide long on can only watch.
FOUR! The slog sweep again! Full and in the arc of Starc, looks to dismiss it out of the park but cannot quite get it over. Beats Broad to his left at wide long on. 16 from the over.
Short ball to start off after the drinks break, Lyon goes for the hook but misses.
Another shorter one, this time Lyon chooses the smart option as he just opens the face of his bat and plays the upper cut. It falls just short of the man at third man and the batters take a single.
Outside off, left alone by Starc.
Bouncer again! Starc does well to evade it.

EDGED AND SIX! This is a shorter one outside off, Starc goes for the pull but top edges it towards third man. Buttler goes for a diving effort on the fence but the ball just goes past him and past the boundary ropes for a six.
The batsman has played it to the point region. They manage to come back for the second.
Full and around middle, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. They pick up a single.
Tossed up around leg, he flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Full and floated outside off, pushed towards cover.
On the pads of Starc, he flicks it towards mid on for a single.
This time on the pads of Lyon, he flicks it towards square leg and takes one.
Bouncer by Archer, Lyon uses the upper cut to flash it over the keeper. The man from third man runs to his left and mops it up as the batters take one.
Another bouncer, Starc does well to evade it.
FIFTY FOR STARC! His 10th in Tests and he is pushing Australia towards 500. On the pads of Starc, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single to get to his fifty.
The batsman goes after this one but misses the line completely.
Short of a length outside off, Lyon cuts it towards point where Denly dives and saves at least a couple for his side.
Another shorter one by Archer, Lyon goes for the pull but misses it completely.
Full and outside off, Starc gets down and hoicks it away to deep mid-wicket for a single. The stand is worth 40 from 32 balls.
Around off, tucked through mid-wicket for a quick single.
Full and outside off, spinning away off the rough, Mitchell looks to swing hard but misses.
Outside off, punched straight to cover.
Full and outside off, MS swings hard but misses again.

Run out missed. Full and outside off, Starc looks to swing hard again and now he connects. Jason Roy is stationed at deep mid-wicket and he returns a good throw to Root. It is a late call from Starc and Lyon is not ready. Sets off late and is gone for all money. But Root, aiming to collect and back-flick it onto the stumps, but misses.
Length ball outside off, Lyon goes for a wild swipe towards mid on but misses it completely.
Short delivery by Archer, Lyon pulls this towards the leg side.
TOP EDGED AND FOUR! Another bouncer by Archer, Lyon goes for the wild pull but he gets a top edge on it. The ball skies and goes behind towards the third man fence on one bounce.
Length ball on middle and off, Lyon tries to block it out but gets a thick inside edge on it as the ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters take one.
Length ball on off, blocked out.
Another length ball outside off, Starc blocks it out towards mid off.

FOUR BYES! Floated just outside the leg pole, Lyon goes for the sweep but it misses everything. Bairstow fails to collect it and so does Broad who puts in a dive to the right side of him from short fine leg. It races towards the fence.
Full and floated on middle and leg, Lyon sweeps it towards square leg and takes a single.
Starc punches this off the back foot.
This time Starc plays the slog sweep and takes a single.
FOUR! Lyon comes down the track to this floated ball on middle and off. He smashes it towards mid-wicket as the ball crosses the fence on one bounce.
Swept by Lyon towards fine leg and the batters take one. And that's it, Tim Paine has signalled for the declaration. Australia end their innings at 497/8.
Full and outside off, Burns lets it go through.
Around off, in line of the stumps, swinging in slightly solidly defended.
Sprayed wide outside off, left alone easily.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Another one off the radar, well outside off, a comfortable leave.
A better final ball to finish an erratic opening over. Full and just outside off, swinging away, Rory thinks about playing at that but then bails out.
A length ball outside off, coming in, Denly shoulders arms and is hit on the thigh pad.
In the Hazlewood corridor of uncertainty, Denly looks to feel it but misses as the ball just misses the outside edge.
Outside off, quietly left alone.

A length ball outside off, Joe comes forward to defend but this is a Hazlewood special. After getting three inswingers, he bowls an outswinger, making Denly play at one which the latter thinks will swing in. Doesn't and misses the outside edge.
ENGLAND ARE AWAY. Full and outside off, JD pushes it towards cover with soft hands and takes a quick single.
A short ball, on middle and leg, Burns ducks but the ball hits his left forearm before lobbing to Matthew Wade at short leg.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, pretty wide, easily left alone.
This is even wider outside off, Joe is happy to leave that alone.
There comes the short ball. Straight, at the body, Denly takes his eyes off the delivery and looks to fend ungainly. The ball hits his glove and then his left shoulder, before dropping down.
Full and outside off, a nice free-flowing drive, but straight to short extra cover.
A length ball, around off, swinging in, JD looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
A length ball, around middle, Burns works it with the inward movement towards fine leg for a single. Both openers off the mark now.
Around off, watchfully defended.
That is a good one from Hazlewood. He bowls this on a length outside off, gets Denly to feel for it and then makes the ball to nip off the seam. Beats the outside edge by a whisker.

Massive appeal for LBW! Turned down. Paine looks at Hazlewood who grits his teeth and indicates it to be going down the leg side. Ball Tracker confirms. A length ball, outside off, Denly looks to defend but the cherry comes back in a long way and goes past the inside edge to hit him on the pads.
Outside off, pretty wide, Joe goes searching for it and misses.

Much better from both players. Hazlewood keeps the line around off while Denly keeps his bat well inside the line. He is still beaten as the ball moves away but at least in this case, he did not go searching for the ball. Josh smiles and mutters some words to Denly.
Cummins is welcomed into the attack with a nice push. Outside off, Burns leans and eases this through the covers. Cover and point track it down and the batsmen take three on the long boundary.
Around off, on a length, solidly defended.
More runs. Short and wide from Cummins, Denly punches it through the covers. Three more.
Way down the leg side, left alone.
Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on for a single.
Outside off, played straight to point.
Length ball on the hips of Burns, he pushes it down onto the pitch and goes straight to short leg.
Length ball outside off, Burns blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Burns takes a foot towards the line of the delivery but then leaves it alone.
Bouncer by Hazlewood now. Burns almost knew it was coming and does well to duck under it.
What a jaffa! Short of a length ball pitching on leg, the ball kept on going away from Burns. He tried to hop and play but is beaten by the movement by just a whisker.
NO BALL! On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards square leg. However, Hazlewood has overstepped and this is signalled as a no ball by the umpire.
Beaten again! Burns again plays inside the line of the delivery to this length ball outside off.
JD has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Length ball way outside off, Denly leaves it alone.
