Beaten! Length ball just around off, it pitches and moves away. Denly plays inside the line and is beaten.
The ball sneaks through the gap between bat and pad and beats the batsman.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sharp catch by Matthew Wade and Joe Denly is a goner! This is on a length, on middle and leg, Denly looks to tuck it towards the leg side but does so uppishly and straight towards Wade at short leg. It goes quickly towards him, hits him on the chest and the ball bounces out. Wade is quick to react and he dives to his right full stretch to gobble up the ball. Australia get the first wicket that they desperately wanted today and it is delivered by Hazlewood.
Fuller on the pads, Overton drives it towards mid on and gets off the mark with a couple.
Around off, solidly defended.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Burns rocks back and cuts it through point for a boundary!
Outside off, Rory looks to cut but this time finds point.
FOUR! Off the bottom edge! Short and outside off, Burns looks to cut but gets a bottom edge past the keeper to the third man fence.
Wide outside off, left alone.

Short and outside off, RB cuts it behind point. Travis Head gives it a good chase from backward point and pulls it back in with a slide. Fumbles while returning the ball but the batsmen are happy with two.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Overton.
Play and a miss! Length ball just outside off, Overton looks to block it out off the front foot but does so inside the line of the delivery and is beaten.
On the hips of Overton, he flicks it towards leg gully uppishly but it falls just short.
Again on the pads of Overton, he pushes this towards mid on.
Down the leg side, Craig pushes this towards fine leg and takes a single. Burns on strike now.
Around the wicket for the last ball of the over. Bouncer on the last ball of the over but way down the leg side. Burns lets it through to the keeper.
Outside off to start the over by Hazlewood, Overton leaves it alone.
Bouncer this time, mixing it up. It is down the leg side and Overton ducks under it.
Good length ball now, pushed back towards the bowler.
Full and around off, blocked out by Craig.
Bouncer down the leg side by Hazlewood, Craig lets it through to Paine.
A bouncer outside off, Overton sways away from the line of the bouncer and lets it pass. STUMPS ON DAY 2, England 23/1, trail by 474!
A short one to start with this is on the body, Burns looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the thigh pad.
This is a good nut! Slightly shorter though, it pitches and straightens. Burns plays it well by taking his hands out of the way.
A little too wide outside off, it is left alone.
Finds the edge but well short! Better from Starc. This is on a length and on off, it shapes away a touch. Burns looks to defend with soft hands but it goes off the outer half to third slip.

That was close! This is angled into the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Starc appeals but the umpire shakes his head. Paine walks up to his bowler but Starc indicates that it is going down leg. Rightly so as Ball Tracker confirms the same. It looked close initially though.
A dot to end! Shorter and on middle, the batter stands tall and keeps it out. A maiden to begin with by Starc.
Starts off with a good length delivery and on off, Overton defends it. Good bounce there for Hazlewood as he hit the higher part of the bat.
A solid punch to get the first runs of the day! This is slightly fuller and on off, Overton pushes it through covers for two.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! 50th Test wicket for Hazlewood against England in Tests. The nightwatchman is out of here and early on. Perfect start for the Australians as had Overton hung out there, it would have really frustrated them. Another length delivery by Hazlewood, this is angled into the batter. Overton looks to defend it but does so with hard hands. The ball straightens, goes off the outside edge quickly to Smith at second slip who makes no mistake.
Off the mark is Root! Not in convincing fashion! This is on a good length and around off, it comes back in. Root looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge towards fine leg for one.
A good short one! Seen that being bowled to Burns quite a lot. Rory ducks under it.
Beauty! Uses the angle well. This is on a length and on off, it slants away. Burns tries to defend but due to the angle away, he gets beaten. End of a top first over by Hazlewood.
2 balls, 2 singles for Root! On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
Another good ball! This is around off but a touch shorter. Burns looks to defend but then sees it moving away so pulls his bat back.
Slightly fuller and on off, no swing for Starc. Burns keeps it out.
Sharp, sharp bouncer! On middle, Burns at the end, evades it.
Another full ball on middle, Burns pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! First boundary of the day! Lovely shot. This is fuller and on off, it is a half volley. Burns creams it through covers and it races away to the fence.
Almost gets Root another time! Not a shot Root needs to play early on. This is fuller and outside off, it shapes away a little. Root looks to stroke it through covers but misses.
Close! This is just outside off and it is coming back in. Root makes a good leave by covering his off pole.

Another good leave! This is just outside off once again, comes back in. Root leaves it on length and the ball goes over the off pole. Two good leaves by Root after playing a loose shot on the first ball.
Now Hazlewood goes fuller and on middle, Root pushes it to mid on.

Four running runs! Don't see that often nowadays. A lovely shot though by Root. This will make him feel good. Fuller and on off, Root strokes it through covers. Wade at extra cover, gives it a chase and pulls it back in before it crosses the ropes. The batters though run four.
That stayed low! Outside off and on a length. Root looks to defend but is beaten due to the low bounce.
Good delivery! This is on a length around off, it shapes away. Burns defends inside the line and gets beaten.
This is on the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Extremely full, almost a yorker on off. Burns jams it out.
Back of a length and on off, Burns stands tall and keeps it out. Starc's lines have been good today, he just needs to get it a touch fuller.

Like that! A little too wide this time but he got the batter playing at it. Also, clever bowling. He kept angling it into the batter. This time gets it to leave him. The length is also a driving one and outside off. RB looks to drive but is beaten.
That is a beauty! This is on a length and around off,  shapes away nicely. Burns' outside edge is beaten as he tries to block.
Outside off and coming back in. Does not come in enough though to make the batter play.
Attacks the stumps this time, Root gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it on a length and around off, Hazlewood wanted it to straighten after pitching but that does not happen. Root defends it.
FOUR! Deft! Nicely played! Shorter and outside off, Root goes back and plays it late. He guides it past third slip and the ball races away to the third man fence.
The slip cordon gets excited but nothing from the bowler! This is behind a length, it lands on middle and then jags back in. Root looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
A short one to end but it is outside off, left alone.
On middle, Burns pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! A freebie but it still has to be put away! A full toss on off, Burns says thank you very much and creams it through covers for a boundary.
A couple now! On the pads, looking to hit the pads of Burns but it is too straight this time. Burns works it through square leg for two.
Extremely full again and on off, it is jammed out.
Shortens his length now by a long way, Burns works it around the corner for two.
One more short ball outside off, Burns spots it early and sways away.
Full again and tailing back in. Root strokes it to mid off.
This starts on off and it tails back in. Root defends it onto the ground.
A scrambled seam delivery, shorter in length. It is just outside off. Root initially looks to poke at it but then bails out.
Down the leg side, Root looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad. Paine dives to his left but does not stop it cleanly. A leg bye is taken as the ball goes towards fine leg.
Back of a length and on middle, the batter stands tall and keeps it out.
Well kept! This is fuller and on the pads, it swings in further. Burns misses the flick. Paine does well to dive to his right and stop it. Not cleanly but no runs conceded.
Fuller and on off, Root strokes it to mid off.
Length this time but outside off, Root lets it be.
Almost drags it on! This is a back of a length ball on off, comes back in a little. Root looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his boot and then it rolls away from the stumps.
BEATEN! Not a lot you can do there. It is angled into off, lands on a length and then moves away. Root defends the original trajectory and gets beaten.
On the shorter side and on off, Root stands tall and keeps it out.
Slightly fuller and on off, Root though gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Flatter and on middle, Burns pushes it to covers. Paine liked the way Lyon starts his spell.
A little extra bounce there! It is slightly shorter and on off, Burns goes back and guides it to point.
Well bowled! This starts on leg, pitches and then turns away. Burns gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Slows it up nicely and bowls it on middle, blocked.

Risky, risky shot. This is flatter and on middle, it is the arm ball. Burns goes back and he initially looks to hit it on the off side but seeing it skid through, he keeps it out by getting his bat down.
A single to end! Burns brings the sweep shot out. He hits it through square leg for one. Not a lot of purchase for Lyon in his first over.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Shorter and on the body, Burns gets on top of the bounce and nudges it to short leg. Played that nicely.
One more short ball on off, it is evaded nicely.
Third bumper in a row, this time it is closer to the body. Burns looks to move out of the way but it hits the arm and goes to the keeper. Three bouncers in a row, a yorker now?
Nope, he bowls it on a length. Burns is solid in defense.
A nasty delivery to end! Shorter and it gets big on the batter. Burns somehow tries to fend at it but the ball hits the body and goes on the off side. A nasty over by Cummins comes to an end.
Turn there! It is bowled way too wide outside off though. Root lets it be.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Root cuts it but to point.
Flatter and on off, Root pushes it to covers.
Loopy ball on off, Root prods forward and keeps it out.
Turn again! This lands outside off and spins back in. Root goes back and defends it.
Loopy ball to end on off, Root is solid in defense again.
One more short one outside off, Burns drops his hands and lets it be.
No ball! Pat oversteps! 50 up for England. They trail by another 447. Shorter and on the body this time, Burns ducks under it.
One more bumper angling across from the middle pole. Burns drops his hands once again and lets it go.
This one is down the leg side, the batter looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length and on the pads. Burns looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
The barrage of short balls continue. Burns spots it though and ducks under it.
One more short one to end! Evaded. Maybe, Cummins is getting too predictable here but he has had success against Burns bowling such deliveries.
Loopy ball on off, it is pushed towards cover.
Another tossed up ball on off, Root keeps it out again.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Quicker again and on off, Root goes back once again and defends it.
Root steps down the track now and looks to work it with the turn but misses to get hit on the pads.
A single to end as Root works it around the corner.
Length ball outside off, Root initially looks to play at this one but bails out at the last moment.
FOUR LEG BYES! Bad ball by Cummins! This one is on the pads, Root looks to flick it towards the leg side and misses. The ball kisses his thigh pads and goes towards the fine leg fence.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
FOUR! Again on the pads of Root, this time he flicks it towards square leg and the ball goes towards the fence in a jiffy.
Fullish this time just outside off, Root defends it out.
Another one fuller and outside off, Root blocks it out. Good over for England, 8 off it.
On the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Floats it up and lands it on middle, Burns pushes it to mid on.
Shorter and outside off, Burns goes back and slaps it through cover-point for one.
FOUR! Too fine! It is on the pads, Root works it fine on the leg side and the ball races away to the fence.
Well bowled! This is tossed up on off, it turns into the batter. Root looks to defend but it goes off the inner half but well short of short leg.
One more tossed up ball on off, Root stretches forward and keeps it out.
Good length ball on the off pole line, Burns looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
FOUR! Good pull shot by Burns! Short and on the leg pole line, Burns gets into position and pulls the ball all along the ground towards the fine leg boundary.
Another good length ball just outside off, blocked out.
Way wide down the leg side, Burns does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
This time length ball outside off, left alone again.
Length ball closer to the body this time, Burns defends it towards point.
Almost! This lands on off, Root looks to defend but the ball turns back in. Goes off the inside edge and onto the pads but lands well away of short leg.
Pushes it through on off, Root goes right back and keeps it out.
Sharp turn! This is on middle, it turns into Root. He looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Sharp turn again! This one though is down the leg side. Root lets it be.
Floats it up on middle, Root works it with the turn to mid-wicket.

OHHH! Good nut to end! This is quicker and flatter outside off, the ball pitches and spins back in at pace. Root fails to put bat on ball as he tries to drop it on the off side. He gets hit on the thigh pad. Lyon really got good purchase in the last over. Good signs for Lyon.
Back of a length and on middle, it is kept out.
Shorter and on the body, Burns ducks under it.
Good length now on off, Burns blocks it out.
Well fielded! This is shorter and outside off, Burns plays it nicely. Gets on top of the bounce and guides it towards point where the fielder makes a good stop.
Shortish and down the leg side, the batter lets it be.
On the body, it is tucked down to fine leg for one.
Flatter and on off, it is guided through point for one.
A little short and on off, Root goes back and pulls but finds the man at short fine leg. It was not off the middle but off the inner half.
Gives it nice amount of air and lands it on off, Root pushes it to covers.
Played to mid-wicket region by the batsman.

It lands on off and it is once again fuller. Root looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Root needs to be careful. He was dismissed in a similar manner in the last Test where he tried to flick but got an inside edge onto the pads and he was taken at slips.
A dot to end as Root blocks it out.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for two.
A bumper but down the leg side, it is ducked under.
Shortish in length and on off, it angles away. Burns hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
One more ball on off, Burns blocks it out.
That hits the shoulder! On the short side, Burns is a touch late to duck under it. It hits the shoulder and goes to the keeper.

Three runs and up comes the 50-run stand. A good one as England were in a spot of bother. This is on the pads, Burns works it towards square leg. The fielder there dives to his left and gets a hand to it. Saves a run for his side.
Full and floated on the pad, pushed towards mid on.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Full and floated outside off, Root looks to paddle this one towards fine leg but misses.

Root survives! Tossed up way outside off, trying to induce the shot from Root and he obliges. He goes for the slap towards cover but gets an inside edge on it and the ball misses the leg pole by a whisker.
Shorter this time, Root shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
This time fuller and on off, pushed towards the off side.
Full and way outside off, Burns leans forward and pushes it towards the cover region beautifully and takes a couple.
Down the leg side this time, Burns lets it be.
FOUR! Graceful by Burns! This is short of a length and outside off, Burns rocks onto the back foot and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Full and on the pads, Burns flicks it off his pads towards fine leg and takes a couple. Burns moves to 49 with this.

FOUR! FIFTY UP FOR BURNS! A great innings and exactly what England needed. This is a length ball outside off, Burns just opens the face of his bat and guides it down towards the empty third man region for a boundary. His 4th Test fifty but his job is half done yet as England will be looking to reduce the deficit as much as they can.
Bouncer! Last ball of the over and Burns ducks under it as the ball goes to the keeper. Good over for England as 12 runs came off it.
Loopy ball on off, Root defends it onto the ground.
Again sharp turn! This lands on off and then spins back in a long way. Root looks to flick but misses.
Out comes the sweep, Root sweeps it through backward square leg for two.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball outside off, Root stretches and gently pushes it towards cover for one.
Shorter and around off, Burns goes back and pushes it to covers.
Shorter and width on offer, Burns opens the face and guides it behind point for three.
FOUR! Runs flowing now! Poor ball. Easy pickings for Root. It is on the pads, Root tucks it fine on the leg side and bags a boundary.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
More runs! 100 up for England. Easy-peasy again. Full and on the pads, it is worked through square leg for another three.
Bouncer this time around the middle pole line, Burns ducks under it.
One more short one outside off, Burns does not play at it.
Tossed up ball outside off, spinning in. Root tucks it towards the leg side.

EDGED AND FOUR! Missing the off stump this time by just a whisker. This one is again pitched outside off and it spins back in sharply. Root tries to open the face of his bat and guide it down towards third man but the ball is too close for that. It takes the inside edge and misses the off pole as the ball goes towards the fine leg fence.

CLOSE! The ball strikes Root very low on the pads as he looks to flick this ball on the pads. It rolls towards the leg side where the fielder picks it up. Burns is halfway down the track  as he wants a run but is sent back. The throw from the fielder is wide of the stumps at the bowler's end hence, Burns makes it back in.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Floated on off, swept away down the leg side.
Shorter this time, Burns defends it towards point and takes a single. Good running!
Good length ball outside off. Root blocks it out.
Length ball outside off, Root opens the face of the bat and guides it down to third man for a single.
Another length ball around off, this time to Burns. He defends it well.
Down the leg side by Starc, Burns looks to flick it but misses.
Fuller and on the pole, Burns pushes it towards mid on.
Again full and around off, pushed towards mid off this time. 1 run off the over.
Tossed up outside off, Root prods forward and pushes this towards cover. Thinks about a run but then opts against it.
This time Root does take the single. Similar ball, Root plays this wide of cover-point and takes a quick single.
Short and outside off to Burns, he guides it to the man at point.
Another one outside off, Burns guides it towards cover-point.
Tossed up on middle, pushed back.
Flatter and on middle, Burns pushes this one towards mid on. Lyon dives to his left in an attempt to save it but the ball goes through him.
Length ball on off, pushed towards point.
Fuller this time, Root pushes this towards the man at mid on.
Outside off, Root guides it towards point off the front foot.

OUCH! That must have hurt Root hard. Length ball on middle and leg, Root tries to block it out but misses to get hit on the box. He is down on the ground in pain but he looks fine as he is soon up on his feet. Root is taking a breather and rightly so.
Length ball way outside off, Root leaves it alone. Starc has been a little bit haywire with his lines so far today.
Length ball outside off, Root cuts it towards point.
Good length ball on the pads, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, Burns prods forward and looks to push this towards cover but this hits the inside half of his bat and the ball goes towards mid on.
Fuller this time by Josh on off, Burns tucks it towards mid on.
Length ball outside off, Burns defends it onto the pitch and looks for a single but Root sends him back.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it uppishly towards backward square leg where Labuschagne is positioned. He fumbles while collecting the ball and the batters take an easy two.
Down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses.
Length ball outside off, Root tries to guide it towards third man but does not get enough on it. The ball goes on the bounce towards Steven Smith as he parries it towards the third slip.
FOUR! This time Root gets it right as he guides this one between point and third slip towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Length ball on middle and off, blocked out by Root.
On the pads of Root, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Hit on the pads but probably going down leg. Starc pitches this around off and gets it to nip back in, Burns misses his defense and is hit on the pads.
This time Burns defends it well and towards mid on off the front foot.
Fullish outside off, pushed towards point by Root.
Good length ball outside off, Root guides it towards the left of gully by opening the face of the bat. The man there dives to his left and saves a certain boundary.
Good length ball around off, blocked out by Root.
This is way outside off and Root does not fiddle with it.
Good length ball outside off, defended by Root towards point.
On the pads of Root, he takes a single off the last ball and keeps strike.
Good length ball on the leg pole to start off by Cummins, Root flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Short of a length ball outside off, Burns does well as he sways away from it.
Good ball by Cummins, he pitches it around leg and gets it to nip back in. Burns misses his defense and is hit around the box.
Length ball around off, defended towards the off side.
Bouncer this time on the leg pole line. Burns ducks under it.
Fuller this time outside off, Burns looks to defend it but gets the toe-end of the bat and the ball rolls towards the slip cordon.
Full ball outside off, Root defends it towards cover.
Good length ball around middle and off, Root blocks it out.
Slower ball but way down the leg side by Josh, Root looks to flick but misses.
This ball pitches on a length around off, Root does well to defend it as the ball gets low on him.
FOUR! Short of a length ball around off, Root rocks onto the back foot and pulls this one towards square leg for a boundary. The partnership moves onto 97 with that boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Root defends it well.
Nasty! Short ball around off, Burns looks to fend at it initially but tries to leave it in the end. Luckily he is hit on the glove and the ball goes down onto the pitch.
Another bouncer but on the leg pole line, Burns sways from it at the last moment.
Short of a length ball outside off, Burns leaves it alone.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards backward square leg and takes a single.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball, tossed up on the off pole line. It pitches and spins away leaving Burns totally squared up.

100-run stand up between Burns and Root! Short again this time outside off, Burns goes onto the back foot and cuts it towards deep point and takes a couple. A very important stand this one for England and they now trail by 372 runs.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Tossed up on middle and off, blocked out by Burns.
Similar delivery, blocked out again by Burns.
Short of a length delivery outside off, Burns cuts it to the man at point.
Outside off, Root leaves that one alone.
Fuller and outside off, Root defends it.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards point off the front foot by Root.
Beaten! Root looks to put bat on ball on this length delivery outside off, but he misses as he defends inside the line.
BEATEN AGAIN! Beautiful bowling by Cummins here. He looks to defend this one off the back foot but is completely squared up by this length delivery around off as it nips away at the last moment.
Length ball outside off and left alone by Root. AND THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
Floats it up on middle, this is defended out.
Another one tossed up on middle, it is blocked.
Another flighted ball on middle, it is worked to mid on.
FOUR! First boundary of the session! A hit-me ball. Short and outside off, Rory goes back and hammers it through covers for a boundary. A nothing delivery and it got the treatment.
Flatter and on middle, this is blocked again.
A single to end! Another short one outside off, Burns hits it through covers for one.
Outside off, it is left alone.
One more bumper, the batter ducks under it.
One more delivery outside off, it is left alone.
That is a beauty! This lands on off and then moves away. Burns tries to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
This is wider outside off, Burns plays inside the line and lets it be.
One more ball outside off, the batter need not play at those. A maiden but not a threatening one.
On middle, it is worked with the turn to mid-wicket.
This is down the leg side, the batter looks to flick but misses.
Plays the sweep but straight to short fine leg.
Shorter in length and outside off, Root plays it late and towards third man for one.
That is a beauty! It lands on off and then turns away sharply. Burns does nothing wrong as he tries to defend the original trajectory but gets beaten.
Flatter and on off, RB goes back and pushes it to covers.
This is angled into the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one. He moves onto 49.
Back of a length again and on middle, this is defended.
A short one on the body, it is ducked under.
This is angled into the pads, Burns works it down to fine leg for a single.
Good length and on off, Root goes back and guides it towards gully.
That is another lovely delivery! In the corridor of uncertainty. It pitches and straightens. Root is half forward as he tries to defend but gets beaten.
Flatter and outside off, this is guided to point.
Shorter and outside off, this is slapped through cover-point for one.
Flatter and outside off, Root looks to guide it down to third man but Smith at first slip, dives to his right and stops it.

'ROOOOOOOT' goes the crowd as the English skipper gets to a half ton. Leading from the front when his team needed him to do so. Lovely, lovely knock. Started off playing a loose stroke but since then, he has been excellent. Still a long way to go. He is not that good at converting fifties into tons but he needs to do it now. He gets there by working it around the corner for a single and gets to his 44th Test fifty.
Flatter and outside off, this is guided to point.
On the pads, it is worked to square leg.
Full ball on middle and leg, blocked towards the leg side by Root.
Good length ball around off, Root pushes it towards point.
FOUR! Fullish and outside off, Root square drives this one beautifully towards the point region off the front foot and the ball races to the fence.
Length ball on middle and off, blocked out by Root.

FOUR! In between the keeper and the slip fielder! Frustrating for Cummins as on a day where the ball is doing nothing for the bowlers, you would want the fielders to grab any kind of opportunity that comes towards them. This is a gem of a delivery. It is fuller and around off, it shapes away late. Root looks to work it on the leg side but due to the movement, it goes off the outside edge in between keeper and Warner who fail to react and it goes to the third man fence. Maybe, the two failed to react as they did not expect an outside edge there as Root looked to play it on the leg side.
Back of a length and on middle, this is defended onto the ground.
Tossed up on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
FOUR! Another one tossed up around off, Burns gets down on one knee and sweeps this one towards the mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Floated on off, defended by Burns.
Beauty by Lyon! This one is pitched on middle and off, it pitches and spins away. Burns looks to cover drive it but does so inside the line and is beaten.
Fuller this time and darted in, pushed back by Burns.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.

NOT OUT! Height is not an issue but the impact is outside off and it is missing off too. It was a review in desperation to be honest. It never looked close. Australia lose one review. This is on a length and around off, ti straightens. Root is squared up as he tries to defend but misses. He gets hit high on the pads. An appeal follows but the umpire shakes his head. After a discussion between the keeper, the slip cordon and the bowler, Australia review. Replays roll in and Ball Tracker shows the on-field call is the right one.
The batsman has played it to the point region.

FOUR! EDGY! Australia continue to get frustrated! This is on a length again and around off, straightens once again. Root looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge, wide of second slip and into the third man fence.
OHHH! Cummins is making things happen here. He has Root fending at one Root need not. This is shorter and outside off, Root hangs his bat out but gets beaten.

Again! Creating problems for the batter. Cummins bangs it short and on the body, Root initially looks to duck but then he is too late to do so. Fends it away awkwardly. All of a sudden, Root does not look comfortable out there.
The last ball is outside off, it is left alone. End of a top over by Cummins. A very testing one.
Shorter and outside off, this is slapped through covers for one.
On middle, Root works it with the turn to short fine leg.
Loopy ball on off, Root blocks it out.
One more delivery down the leg side, Root works it to short fine leg.
Good fielding! Shorter and on middle, Root goes back and pulls it through backward square leg. The fielder in the deep runs to his right, dives and saves two for his side.
A dot to end as the last ball is worked to mid-wicket.
A short one on the body, Burns lets it be by moving out of the way.

Direct hit and Burns was in trouble! That was very casual from Rory. This is a shorter delivery on off. Burns taps it towards cover and takes off. He is getting to the other end casually. Head picks the ball up and has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses.
Good length and on off, this is kept out.
This is angled into the batter, Root looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards deep square leg for one.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for two.
Another bouncer to Burns and he manages to fend it away again off his glove towards point. He is struggling against the short ball but he is still out there.
Tossed up outside off, Root looks to block it out but gets the inside half of his bat on it.
Floated on off, blocked out by Root.
On the pads of Root, he tucks it towards square leg.
Full and floated on middle, Root looks to block it but gets the toe end of his bat on it.
Full and floated on off, Root gets down on one knee and sweeps it towards square leg for a single.
Short and wide outside off, Burns slaps it towards cover where the fielder dives to his right and stops it.
Play and a miss. This is a length ball outside off, Root looks to cut it towards point but misses the ball completely.
Fuller this time outside off, Root blocks it out.
BEATEN! Length ball outside off, it pitches and swings away leaving Root squared up.
Good ball again by Cummins! This one is on a good length on middle, Cummins looks to block it but he gets an inside edge on it and the ball rolls towards square leg as the batters take a single.
Length ball on middle and off, Burns blocks it out off the back foot.
Some chin music for the batsman, he lets that bouncer through to the wicketkeeper.
Tossed up on the pads of Lyon, he flicks this one towards backward square leg.
Short and outside off, cut to point.
Full and wide outside off, Root defends it out.
Another one full and on off, blocked out.
Shorter this time, on middle and leg. Root pulls it strongly but straight towards the man at squarish mid-wicket.
Outside off, Root leaves it alone.
On off, it is kept out.
Shorter and around off, Burns evades it.
Shorter and on middle, this is ducked under.
Back of a length again and on off, Burns gets right behind and keeps it out.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
This is angled into the batter, Root blocks it solidly.
Shorter and on middle, Burns works it to mid on.
In the air... but safe! Burns looks to sweep this ball on middle, there is extra bounce though and a top edge is induced. It lands safe in the fine leg region for one.
Floats it up on off, Root defends it onto the ground.
Shorter and on middle, Root pulls it through square leg for one.
Shortish and outside off, Burns goes back and cuts it through point for one.
A single to end as Root works it with the turn through mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, Root guides it to point.
Another one on a length and on middle, Root goes back and keeps it out.
Another ball on a good length and around off, Root guides it to point.
On a length and outside off, Root blocks it from within the crease.
Back of a length and outside off, Root defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery around off, Root blocks it by coming on the front foot.
On off, Burns defends it onto the ground.
Flatter and on off, Burns guides it to point.

Is that a dropped catch? No, it was just short. Shorter and outside off, it is turning away. Burns goes back and slaps it hard but it lands just short of Wade at covers who dives to his right. He fails to stop it and a run is taken.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
This is bowled outside off and it is turning back in. Root goes back and keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, it pitches and then moves away. Beats the outside edge of the batter's bat.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! At last, Australia have managed to break the stand. It has been a good passage of play for them, they started to trouble the English batters and have got the reward. End of the 141-run stand and the Aussies are pumped up. Burns misses out on his ton by 19 runs. Once again excellent use of the angle by Hazlewood. It is on a length and around off, going away with the angle. Burns looks to defend but does so inside the line. It goes off the outside edge towards second slip where Smith takes a good catch. Second wicket for Josh and Australia would hope, this opens the floodgates. England trail by another 331 runs.
Almost another! This is on a length and around off, comes back in a touch. Roy looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle this time, Roy pushes it to the man at mid on.
Just outside off, it is left alone.
On the fuller side and on off, Roy pushes it nicely to the man at mid off. End of a successful over by Hazlewood.
On middle, Root works it to short leg.
Shorter and on middle, it is pulled towards deep square leg for one.
Close again! Roy has started nervously. This lands outside off and spins back in sharply. Roy looks to defend but once again gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Flatter and outside off, Roy guides it to point.
On middle, it is worked with the turn to mid-wicket.
Flatter and shorter outside off, Roy stands tall and guides it to point.
Just outside off, Root opens the face of the bat and guides it on the off side for one.
Back of a length and on off, it straightens a touch. Roy is squared up as he tries to defend. It goes off the outer half towards point.
Outside off and it is left alone.
FOUR! That is authoritative! Roy should feel really good after that shot. It is a length ball around off, Roy strides forward and strokes it on the up through covers for a boundary.
Good fielding by Starc! Three for Roy. This is on the pads, Roy works it through backward square leg. Starc runs to his left, dives and pushes it back in.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb in front! Pin-drop silence here. Root is a goner and once again he fails to convert his half ton into a ton. However, there is not a lot he could have done here. This lands just outside off and it jags back in sharply. Root looks to defend off the back foot but the ball stays low. He misses and is hit right in front of the pad. An appeal and up goes the finger. Root walks back straightaway as he knows he is a goner. Hazlewood gets him once again. Both the batters who were batting nicely are back in the hut.
Floats it up outside off, Roy looks to defend but the ball turns back in and it goes off the inside edge onto the pads.
This is pushed to mid on.
FOUR! Slapped! Another boundary for Roy. Shorter and outside off, Roy goes back and hits it hard through covers for a boundary.
Works it with the turn through mid-wicket for one. Good batting.
On middle, Stokes gets right behind the line and keeps it out.

Edge but just short! This is tossed up on off, it pitches and turns away. Stokes looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge and falls just short of second slip who dives to his right. He makes a good stop though with one hand.
On off, Roy pushes it to mid on.
That is a beauty! This is angled into the off pole which means the batter has to play at it. He looks to defend but the ball moves away and beats the outside edge.
Fuller and on off, the batter strokes it nicely to mid off.
This is angled into the pads, Roy works it through mid-wicket and takes two.
Outside off, it is left alone.
This is on the pads, Roy looks to flick but misses. It hits the pads and rolls towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Tossed up on off, pushed towards long on for a single.
On the pads this time, Stokes flicks it towards backward square leg and takes a single to get off the mark.
Floated one outside off, Roy pushes this through the covers. The fielder in the deep fumbles and also throws poorly which allows the batters to take an easy three.
Good ball by Lyon. Pitched on off pole line, it spins away from Stokes. He is beaten by the turn on that and is left completely squared up.
Shortish and outside off, Stokes punches this towards cover and takes a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Nasty! That took out of nowhere! Shorter and on middle, it takes off after pitching. Stokes somehow fends it away down to fine leg for one.
Shorter and outside off, the batter guides it to point.
A rash shot! Shorter and outside off, Roy looks to drag his pull through the leg side but misses.
Back of a length and on off, Roy pushes it to mid off.
This is angled into the pads, Roy looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.

A huge appeal but not given! In the end, it was an excellent take by Paine. It lands on off and then turns away. There is also extra bounce. Stokes looks to defend but misses. Paine somehow manages to hang onto it. He appeals but the umpire shakes his head. Ultra Edge shows nothing.
Floats it up on off, Stokes keeps it out.
The batsman has driven it straight down the ground.
Shorter and around off, Stokes goes back to defend but the ball turns away and goes off the outer half towards point.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it fine on the leg side for two.
On middle, Stokes lunges and keeps it out.

Another appeal but not given! This lands outside off and jags back in. Roy fails to put bat on ball. It hits him high on the pads and lobs towards second slip. There is an appeal for a catch but it is turned down.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
FOUR! Nice shot! Short and outside off, Roy stands tall and punches it through covers. No stopping those. He got on top of the bounce really nicely.

OUT! Roy is cleaned up! That is a jaffa of a delivery! Three wickets in quick time. Hazlewood gets another. This lands on a length and around off, Roy looks to push at it, once again, he tries to connect with the ball way ahead of his pad. The ball though jags back in, sneaks between bat and pad and knocks the middle pole over. Lovely sight for a bowler. England in a spot of bother now. Still another 102 runs to avoid the follow-on. They have half the side back in the hut. Also, the new ball will be available in a few overs. Australia will be looking for a couple more wickets before the end of play.
Welcomes the new batter with a bumper, Bairstow ducks under it.
JB is off the mark! This is fuller and around off, Bairstow plays inside the line, it goes off the outer half through backward point for two.
Tossed up outside off, Stokes cuts it towards cover as the batters take two. 200 up for England with this and they need less than 100 runs now to avoid the follow on.
Shorter this time, Stokes blocks it out.
Tossed up and full outside off, Stokes pushes it out.
Stokes has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Short by Lyon again, pushed towards point by Stokes.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Starts off with a length ball outside off, Bairstow makes a leave.
First run of the day! A good delivery this! It is on off and comes back in a touch. Bairstow looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through backward square leg for one.
Good leave! This was very close to the off pole, the length was a touch shorter. Stokes lets it be.
Another ball on a length and just outside off, Stokes watches it carefully and lets it be.
FOUR! Stokes gets off the mark today in style! A short one but it bounces at a comfortable height for the the batter. Stokes swivels and pulls it behind square and bags a boundary. First of the day.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Flatter and around off, Bairstow blocks this one out.
Floated outside off, this turns back in. Bairstow defends this one well back towards Lyon.
Similar ball, Bairstow again does well to push it out.
This one spins too much and goes down the leg side. Bairstow leaves it alone.
On the pads of Bairstow, he flicks it towards fine leg.
Another one on the pads, Bairstow flicks this one towards deep square leg and takes a single.
BEATEN! Well bowled by Cummins! This is a length ball outside off, Bairstow looks to block this one but is beaten as he does so inside the line. The ball misses his bat by just a whisker.
Outside off, left alone by Bairstow.
On the pads of Bairstow, he flicks it towards mid-wicket but straight to the man.
Outside off again by Cummins, left alone by JB.
Fuller this time, attacking the off pole, Jonny pushes it back towards Cummins.
This time pulls it back, Bairstow blocks this one off the back foot towards cover.
Tossed up outside off, left alone by Stokes.
Darted into the off pole, Stokes blocks it out.
Another one on the off pole line, Ben pushes it towards point.
Outside off by Lyon, Ben opts to leave this one alone.
Shorter this time, Stokes goes onto the back foot and cuts this one towards cover-point for a single.

Loud appeal by Australia for an LBW! Lyon pitches this one way outside off and gets it to turn back in. Bairstow pads it out but. The visitors appeal but nothing from umpire Erasmus. Australia mull over taking the review but decide against it as Lyon thinks it is going over. Ball Tracker comes in and confirms that. It though was a brave leave by Bairstow. A touch fuller and he might have been in trouble.
Good length ball in the channel, very close to the off pole actually. Stokes leaves it alone.
Beaten this time! Stokes was tempted seeing the room outside off on this length ball. He leans into the drive to cream it through the covers but the ball shapes away to beat the outside edge.
On the hips on a shortish length. Stokes works it through square leg for a run.
Shortish length on off, Bairstow shoulders arms and sees the ball shape further away as it goes to Paine behind the wicket.

Poor fielding there from Hazlewood. This is a fullish length ball on middle and leg, Bairstow flicks it off his toes wide of Hazlewood at mid on. He should've cut it off but he is late in his slide and the ball goes through towards long on. They take three. Hazlewood returns the ball and hits the stumps with the direct hit but the batter was well in. The ball deflects towards cover after hitting the stumps. Bairstow thought to steal another run but decided against it.
Good length ball outside off, tapped towards cover this time by Stokes.
Darted just outside off, pushed towards mid on by Bairstow for a single.
Floated on off, Stokes blocks it out.
On the pads of Stokes, he flicks it towards the man at square leg.
Floated outside off again, Ben pushes this towards extra cover.
Tossed up on the pads, Stokes pushes this towards mid on.
Defended off the front foot by Stokes back to the bowler.
Length ball outside off, Bairstow pushes it to point.
Length ball outside off, Bairstow leaves it alone. Not much movement off the first ball though.
Fuller this time, Bairstow pushes this towards the man at cover.
Length ball just around off, Bairstow knows exactly where his stumps are and makes the leave.
On the pads of Bairstow, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Good first over by Starc. He bowls this last ball on a good length and Stokes blocks it out.

BEATEN! Superb ball to start off by Hazlewood. This one pitches outside off and nips back in. Bairstow looks to defend but misses and is hit high on the pads. The Aussies appeal but nothing from the umpire. Maybe going over and yes, Ball Tracker confirms it.
Another one just outside off, this time on a length. It again nips back in and JB is hit high on the thigh pad.
FOUR! Good reply by Bairstow! Hazlewood bowls this a touch fuller and Bairstow pounces at it as he drives this through mid off for a boundary. Wade at mid off dives to his right but fails to stop it.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Bairstow but this was mightily close to the stumps.
On the pads of Bairstow, Jonny works it down the leg side.
Length ball on middle and leg, Bairstow pushes this towards mid off.
Good length ball just around off, Stokes pushes it towards mid on.
Length ball around off, Stokes shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Shorter and outside off, Stokes pulls this one towards deep mid-wicket and takes a couple.

EDGED AND FOUR! Beauty by Starc! This was a scrambled delivery, on a length just outside off. Stokes looks to push this towards the off side but it comes back in just a little. Stokes ends up playing it outside the line, it goes off the inside edge, over the stumps and down to the fine leg fence. Starc would have loved that to deflect onto the stumps. He needs a  wicket to get his confidence up. Luck not going his way for now.

DROPPED! Fuller length ball just around off, Stokes looks to push this back towards the bowler but plays this uppishly. It goes low towards the right of Starc, he fails to get down in time and the ball brushes his finger tips and rolls towards mid off. A tough chance especially for a tall pacer. Two deliveries, two close shaves. Starc getting back to his best?
Fuller this time, Jonny pushes this towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball, closer to the body, Stokes blunts it onto the pitch.
A confident leave from Stokes that one! You have to be absolutely sure about your off pole when you make such a leave. It pitches on off and shapes away as Stokes shoulders arms.

Another beauty! This time it goes past the inside edge. Hazlewood pitches this one on a shortish length and gets it to straighten. Stokes looks to push it with hard hands towards the off side but is beaten. Lucky not to edge that one.
Length ball just outside off, Stokes pushes this towards mid off.
On the pads of Stokes, he works it towards square leg but straight to the man.
Bouncer by Hazlewood to end the over, Stokes ducks under it and lets that one through.
Full and just outside off, JB pushes this straight towards mid on.
FOUR! Length ball just outside off, Bairstow goes onto the back foot and slaps this through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Jonny Bairstow.
Another length ball just outside off, shaping away, Jonny leaves it alone.

OUT! TIMBER! Jaffa by Starc! What a beauty! This is what you will get from Starc, he will bowl a few bad deliveries but he is a wicket-taker and he can produce some gems. Also, it is a much-needed wicket for him, he has not been at his best but that delivery is one which Starc at the top of his game use to bowl. He sets up Bairstow by angling the previous two deliveries away from off. This time, Starc pitches this one fuller and around off, it tails back in late. Bairstow may have been a bit surprised by the movement, he ends up playing all around it, it sneaks through the gate and shatters the stumps. Early wicket for Australia, just what they wanted. The new ball does the trick for them. England still need 70 to avoid the follow-on. 4 wickets in hand.
Wide outside off stump, the batsman leaves it alone. End of a successful over by Starc.
Good length ball outside off, pushed back by Stokes.
On the pads of Stokes, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Beauty by Hazlewood! He gets this one to move away after pitching on a length. Buttler is squared up by this one and it misses the outside edge.
Good length ball coming in towards the batter, he is hit on the thigh pad as he misses his flick.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler cuts it but straight to the man at point.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Length ball on middle and leg, Stokes pushes this towards mid-wicket.
Length ball just outside off, Stokes initially looks to play at it but bails out at the last moment.
Fuller and around off, pushed back towards the bowler.

Good cricket all around! Starc bowls this fuller and around off, it is swinging in the air and difficult to play against. However, Stokes does well to powerfully push it towards mid on. Cummins there dives to his right and parries it towards mid off to save a certain boundary. In the end the batters take one.
Bouncer by Starc, Buttler ducks under it.
Length ball just outside off, Buttler defends it out onto the pitch. He thinks about the single but is sent back by Stokes.
On a fuller length and outside off, Stokes leaves it easily.
Once again on the fuller length and on off, Stokes defends it towards mid on.
TOP EDGE AND FOUR! Bouncer on the body, Stokes looks to pull it but eventually ends up getting a top edge which runs to the fine leg fence.

FOUR LEG BYES! Hazlewood bowls this on a length but the line is down the leg side. Stokes looks to flick it off his pads but misses it. The ball kisses the thigh pad and goes past the diving keeper to the fine leg fence.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Length delivery around off, Stokes defends it off his front foot towards the off side.
FOUR! Fuller in length and outside off, Buttler drives it crisply through covers and the ball races to the long off fence for a boundary. Buttler is off the mark with this.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. One run added to the total.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Starc gets another! He is on fire at the moment and this is probably the biggest wicket of all. Ben Stokes, the star of the England side. Another excellent delivery. The new ball is working wonders for the left-arm pacer. This is an outswinger. It is on a length and around off. Stokes goes back and tries to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge straight to Smith at second slip. He makes no mistake. Australia are ecstatic. Into the bowling all-rounders now are the Aussies. 55 more needed for England to avoid the follow-on. 3 wickets in hand.

RUN OUT CHANCE MISSED! That was very lazy from Archer. A direct hit and it would've been curtains for him. Shortish ball on middle, Archer does well to work it towards square leg and he wants a single. But he looks to reach the non-striker's end by jogging. He is unaware that there is a fielder haring at the ball. The fielder has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. Archer had given up and he is lucky to survive. Eventually a run to get off the mark.
FOUR! Starc overpitches and Buttler takes full toll off it. He drives this fuller one outside off through the cover region and the ball crosses the fence in a flash.
Buttler leaves this length ball outside off and the keeper gathers it. End of a successful over for Australia.
OHHH! This is fuller and around off, it shapes away a touch. Archer looks to defend but is beaten.
Another one on a length and around off, it is kept out.
Shorter and outside off, Archer ducks under it.
Once again it is bowled on off, Archer gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
A short one on the body, it is ducked under.
Another short one outside off, Archer looks to fend at it but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Shorter and outside off, Buttler looks to push it through the off side but ends up getting it off the inner half back to the bowler.

Another beauty! That missed the off pole by a whisker! This is fuller again and it starts outside off. Comes back in late. Buttler looks to force it against the swing. It goes past the inside edge and just past the off pole.
Edgy runs! This one is angled away from the off pole. Buttler looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge past Smith who gets a hand to it. Saves two for his side. 250 up for England.
One more ball outside off, it is left alone.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.

FOUR BYES! Bonus runs for England. They would take it with both hands. This is full and outside off, it pitches and goes along the ground. Paine fails to collect it as he gets some bad bounce and goes to the third man fence.
Tossed up outside off, landing on the foot marks and spinning in. Archer  defends it to short leg.
Flighted delivery outside off, Archer once again defends it to short leg.
Once again spinning in from the foot marks and Archer plays it to the man at short leg.
Spinning in from outside off, Archer fends it awakwardly to the leg side and it is just wide off the man at short leg.
Archer looks to defends this tossed up delivery outside off but fails to lay bat on ball.
Archer defends this flatter ball outside off to the off side.
NO BALL! Cummins has overstepped! This is on middle, Buttler works it wide of mid on for one.
A bumper now! The batter ducks under it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller one outside off, Archer defends it to covers.
On a length and outside off, Archer looks to cut it through point but fails to lay bat on ball. The ball goes past the outside edge.
Length ball around off, Archer defends it by crouching low.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! England 8 down now and they are still 42 away from avoiding the follow-on. Australia right on top at the moment. This though is a needless shot by Archer. This is a nothing delivery. It is short and outside off. Archer earlier in the over, went after one outside off but got away with that. This time too he hangs his bat out again, does not get away with it. It goes off the outside edge to Paine who takes it.
Fuller one on the stumps, Buttler works it straight to mid-wicket.
FOUR!  Loopy delivery outside off, Buttler drives it through the covers. The man at long off runs across but he fails to reach the ball as it crosses the fence.

NOT OUT! It seemed to be missing the off pole to the naked eye and indeed it is missing. Lyon bowls this one way outside off and makes it come back in sharply. Buttler pads this one out and is hit high and outside off. The Australian players appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Lyon and Tim Paine mull over taking the review and go for it at the last possible second. Replays roll in, Ball Tracker comes into play and shows it to be going above the off pole. Australia have lost both their reviews.
FOUR! Flatter and quicker one on middle and leg, Buttler glances it nicely towards the fine leg fence to earn another boundary.
Fuller and flatter, pushed towards mid on.
Quicker one again which turns way down the leg side. Paine fails to collect as the ball goes towards short fine leg. Warner does well to to get to the ball. No runs taken.
Back of a length on off, Broad hops in his crease and defends it to point.
Short of a length delivery outside off, the ball takes the outside edge of Broad's bat and rolls towards third slip.
Broad defends this length delivery outside off towards the off side.
FIVE WIDES! Bouncer! Cummins goes way too short and the line is on the middle stump, Broad leaves it as the ball sails over him and over the keeper to the third man fence.
Once again A short ball. The length is down the leg side. Broad looks to flick but fails to lay wood on the ball.
Broad defends this length ball outside off towards covers and takes a single.

FOUR! Buttler is playing a responsible innings here. He is leaving the good ones and taking full toll off the bad ones. Cummins bowls fuller length delivery outside off and Buttler drives it through point. The ball reaches the fence and Buttler fetches a boundary. A very valuable one though.
A single off the first ball! This is tossed up on off, it pitches and turns away. Broad looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards backward point for one.
Flatter and on off, Buttler goes back and works it through square leg for one.
Shorter and on off, it pitches and turns away. Broad goes back and guides it to point.
Big turn but the line is way too wide outside off, it is left alone.
Another wasteful delivery. Outside off, it is left alone.
A good nut! This is tossed up on off, it pitches and turns away. Beats the outside edge of Broad's bat as he tries to defend.
Length ball outside off, Buttler defends it down to mid off with a straight bat.
Yorker on the pads, Buttler flicks it to mid-wicket and looks for a single but is denied by his partner.
Length delivery on the pads, Buttler flicks it to fine leg and gets a single.
Shorter one on the body, Broad ducks under it awkwardly.
NO BALL! Cummins escaped on the previous one but not this time. Another one which is bowled short and Broad is opened up. He defends  it in a weird way.
Shorter one once again. This is a tactic or are the Australians straying away from the plan. Cummins bowls a short one again and Broad sways away from the line at the last moment.
This time bowls a fuller one and Broad flicks it straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Full length ball outside off, left alone by Jos Buttler.
Good length ball just outside off, Buttler looks to push this towards cover but it goes off the outer half of his bat towards backward point.
Length ball outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to let that one through.
Beauty by Starc! Length ball on the fourth stump line, it straightens after pitching. Buttler looks to defend it off the back foot but the ball sneaks through the bat and his body.
Length ball outside off, left alone.

Brave leave off the last ball this by Buttler! This one is pitched up fuller and just outside off, it nips back in. Jos knows exactly where his stumps are and he shoulders arms to it. It is very close to the stumps but no harm done. THAT IS LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Goes past the outside edge on the first ball. Pitched on middle and turned just a tad bit away from the block of Broad.
Another one turns away as Broad looks to poke. Pitched on the same line and turns away.
Loopy fullish ball on middle, Broad sweeps it towards deep square leg for a couple.
Flatter one outside off, left alone by Broad.
Flatter and quicker this time, Broad comes forward to block.
A flighted ball, Broad looks to push it through point but the ball goes off the outer half of the willow low towards third slip. Good start this from Lyon.
Starts with a fuller ball outside off, Buttler punches it straight to mid off.
Good length on the pads, Buttler tucks it towards fine leg to change ends. He is trusting Broad against Starc.

And Starc goes for the yorker but gets the line wrong as this one is dished on the pads. Broad looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters cross over again.
Full outside off to Buttler, he finds the mid off fielder with his firm drive.
Misses his line this time as this is down the leg side. Buttler looks to flick but can't get bat on it.
Fuller length and coming in, Buttler goes for the drive through cover but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller and on the pads, Broad sweeps but finds the short fine leg fielder.
On middle and on a fuller length, pushed back to the bowler.
A good ball this and it had Broad in two minds. It pitched around off. Broad wanted to sweep initially but decided to block at the end. The ball goes towards square leg off the inner half for a run.
Flatter and quicker but outside off, Buttler lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller ball around off, Buttler blunts it towards the off side.
Quicker one again but too wide to make Buttler play. He lets it go the keeper.
Fuller ball on off, Broad looks to jam this out but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the second slip fielder who does well to stop the ball.
Down the leg side on a good length. Starc will bowl a beauty and then balls like these. Broad looks to work it down the leg side but misses to get bat on ball.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Broad hops and keeps it out.
Beaten! Good shortish ball which has Broad going for the drive. He goes hard at the ball and misses.

OUT! Woodwork disturbed with a beauty! Starc is brilliant against the tail-enders says the commentator on air. He is obviously right as we see Broad's stumps flattened. Fuller ball outside off, it jags back in after pitching and sharply. Broad looks to defend but can't do anything about the movement. It goes between bat and pad and knocks the stumps over. No. 9 down and England still need another 15 to avoid the follow-on. Exciting stuff!
Fuller ball, Leach pushes it towards the bowler.
Flighted ball around off, blocked towards the bowler.
Outside off, floated by Lyon. Buttler looks to defend but misses.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Great ball by Lyon. This one pitches outside off, it spins back in and Buttler misses the line of the delivery. Paine too misses the ball and the ball is gathered by the leg slip fielder.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Buttler slaps this one through covers for a boundary.
On the pads of Buttler, he flicks it towards the leg side.
Good length ball on middle, Leach blocks it towards mid-wicket.
A bumper this time. Leach ducks under it. Don't bowl there and target the stumps says the commentator on air.

FOUR! Leach is a confident man. He had done really well in the last Test during that partnership with Stokes. Shows a glimpse of that here. Starc goes fuller but outside off, Leach drives this through mid off firmly. The ball races to the fence but gets a chase from Mathew Wade. He dives to get the ball back in play and does so. However, the umpire checks with the the third umpire if he was touching the ropes as he tried to get the ball back in. And, yes, he has touched the ropes when in contact with the ball.
Shortish ball outside off, Leach has a poke but misses.
Full ball outside off, kept out this time by Leach.

Huge appeal for LBW. Yes, that's out. But no, that's not out says Marais Erasmus. Leach had survived a LBW call during the last match as well. Australians were without reviews then. They are without review even now. Fuller ball on middle, Leach looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. Starc along with the entire team appeal but Erasmus deems this in the favour of Leach and England. However, had the Australians not wasted the review, they would've had closed this innings as the Ball Tracker shows that this was going to hit the leg pole. Lucky Leach, once again though.
Flatter and outside off, Buttler lets it be.
Tossed up on middle, it is hit back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, Buttler tries to flick but misses. Paine too fails to collect it and it goes to short fine leg.
Floats it up on middle, this is defended onto the ground.
Gets the single which means, Leach has just the one ball to play. On middle, it is worked through square leg for one.
A nothing delivery to end! Outside off, it is left alone.
Full length ball around off, blocked out by Buttler.

Off the inner half and Buttler retains strike. Again full and outside off, Buttler looks to push this towards the off side but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket and the batters take two. More importantly, Buttler on strike.
Buttler tries to push this towards cover but mistimes it. It goes over the fielder at extra cover and the batters take two. 2 more needed to avoid the follow-on.
FOUR! The follow-on has been avoided! Full and wide outside off, Buttler pushes this through covers and the ball races to the fence. They would now look to cut the deficit as much as they can.
Shorter this time and Buttler pulls this one towards square leg for a single.
Last ball of the over and this is on the pads of Leach. He misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler lets it be.
Gets closer to the body of Buttler on a good length. He gets right behind the line of the delivery to block.
Edged but short! Another ball which is closer to the off pole. Buttler looks to defend but gets an outside edge which rolls towards gully on the bounce.
Back of a length ball on middle, Buttler swivels to pull but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Slightly shortish length on middle, Buttler punches it towards mid on.

OUT! Cleans him up with a moving peach! It's a fuller ball which comes back in to Buttler. He stays in the crease and wants to go down town. But as the ball moves in, Buttler plays down the wrong line. The ball goes onto hit the off pole behind. But hello, hold on. They're checking for the front foot no ball. That looks really close but the third umpire feels there's enough behind the line which means Buttler has to walk back. However, he has played a very handy knock. Australia lead by 196 runs.
Broad starts off with a good length ball way outside off, Warner leaves it alone. He will be looking to get him out for the second time in this match.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards point.
On middle and leg this time, Warner takes a step down the track and pushes it towards mid on.

Fiery! Good ball on middle and off, Warner blocks it back towards Broad. He fakes a throw at the stumps and Warner rushes back into the crease. Warner and Broad have a stare at each other first but then exchange smiles in the end.
BEATEN! Warner picked that bouncer up very late. He initially looks to play at it but bails out in the end.

OUT! LBW! Warner is out of here and Broad is the man who has got him again! HIS 300TH TEST WICKET IN ENGLAND. This one is on a good length and just outside off, it comes in with the angle. Warner tries to block it out but misses and he is hit high on the pad. The English players go for the appeal in unison and the umpire gives it out. Warner has a chat with his partner at the non-striker's end but Harris tells him there is no use of taking the review. Ball Tracker comes in and confirms it as it shows three reds. Three consecutive ducks for Warner now and he is in a rough patch of form.
Fuller ball around off, tapped towards mid off by Harris.
Beaten! Goes past the outside edge this time. This is closer to the off pole. It is pitched on off, and shapes away from Harris. He looks to fend it away but misses.
Good length ball this time, Harris covers his stumps and lets it go to keeper.
Good length ball, angled into the batter from off and middle, blocked towards the leg side this time.
No ball! Bouncer but it is too high. Harris ducks under it. However, Jofra has overstepped.
Beats the outside edge again! Another good length ball in the channel, shapes away from Harris' poke to beat the outside edge.
Fuller ball around off, Harris leans into the drive to cream this through covers but Roy does well to save a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus lets it go to the keeper.
In the channel again and on a good length. Marnus lets it go the keeper again.
Slightly fuller and on middle, Marnus gets one hand off the bat handle to drop it towards the leg side with soft hands.

Shortish length ball on off, Labuschagne taps it towards cover and looks for a run. But the fielder is quick at ball. Seeing that Marnus return to his crease. The fielder has a shy at the stumps but misses. He was in anyway.
Fuller and closer to the off pole, Marnus lunges to block it well.
Fuller ball again, gets behind the line to block. Back-to-back maiden from Broad.
OUCH! That one must have hurt Harris. Length ball just outside off, comes in with the angle. Harris looks to push this one towards the on side but misses and is hit on the box.
FOUR! Great reply by Harris! Full and on the pads, Harris drives this one wide of mid on and the ball has raced towards the fence.
Length ball on the body, Harris tucks it towards the leg side and looks for a single but Labuschagne opts against it.
Harris defends this one by presenting the full face of the bat.
Length ball just outside off by Jofra, it pitches and nips away. Harris looks to defend first but then bails out.
Good length ball wide outside off, Harris fends at it but gets an outside edge at it which goes on the bounce towards gully. It goes past the diving fielder and they take a single.

FOUR BYES! Too much movement on that one! It pitches outside off, and starts to come back in with the angle. It goes down the leg side, Harris leaves it and it goes even further away from the keeper. Bairstow's dive cannot stop the ball and it goes to the fine leg fence.
Good length ball outside off, Harris looks to push this towards the off side but gets an inside edge on it. It goes past the leg pole and towards fine leg for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Superb shot! This is a fullish ball outside off, Labuschagne slaps this through covers for a boundary.
Marnus has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads of Labuschagne, he flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length on off, it is kept out.
Outside off, this one is left alone.
On a good length and around off, Marnus goes back and keeps it out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Back of a length and on off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Well bowled and nicely played in the end! Shortish and just outside off, Marnus looks to defend but then there is extra bounce. He does well to drop his hands and lets it go.

OUT! Three reds and Harris is a goner! A waste of a review to be honest, that looked out. This is almost a carbon copy of how Harris got out in the first innings. Broad comes steaming in from around the wicket just like he did in the first innings. He lands it on off and it is slightly fuller, it jags back in. Harris looks to play it with a straight bat but misses and is hit flush on the front pad. An appeal and up goes the finger. Marcus walks up to his partner and after a chat reviews. Replays roll in and they show that the on-field call is the right one. Australia lose a review. Things going good for England at the moment.
Outside off, it is left alone.
That stays low! Well played in the end! This is on off, it skids through. Smith gets his bat down in time and keeps it out. That just shows how carefully Smith watches the ball.
Fuller and around off, Smith strokes it nicely to covers.
This is angled into the batter, Smith works it to mid-wicket.

Smith is off the mark! Broad bowls one full and outside off, Smith looks to stroke it through the off side but then tries to bail out. Too late as the ball hits the bat and rolls through covers for two.
Length ball outside off, Marnus drives it through covers for a couple.
Length ball outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Fuller one around off, Marnus defends it towards the off side.

BEATEN! Good ball by Archer. He bowls one in the channel of uncertainty and Marnus gets sucked into poking at it. But luckily for him the ball goes past the outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.
FOUR! Back of a length and outside off, Labuschagne opens the face of his bat at the last moment and runs it down to third man. The ball crosses the fence to hand a boundary to Australia and Marnus.
Length ball outside off, Labuschagne rises on his toes to defend that into the ground towards the off side.
Just short! Fuller and on middle, Smith looks to drive but the ball sticks in the surface. It goes uppishly but well short of mid on.
Down the leg side, Smith looks to flick but misses.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Cut him into half! This lands outside off and then jags back in. Smith looks to put bat on ball but is beaten.
Shorter and outside off, Smith mistimes his cut to point.
That is a brave, brave leave! This is fuller and outside off, it comes in. Smith leaves it and it goes just past the off pole.
Good length in the channel outside off, Marnus lets it go to the keeper.
Gets closer this time on a good length. Marnus blunts it towards mid off by getting right behind the line of the ball.

OUT! That looked dead plumb! Marnus knew it as soon as he was hit on the pads. England are on fire! This time it is Jofra Archer. Fuller and straight this time. Marnus looks to defend but the ball shapes in late to miss the forward block. He is hit on the pads. Archer and England make a loud appeal along with the crowd. The umpire agrees and sends him packing. He though consults with Smith and eventually goes for the review. This looks close, very close. The Ultra Edge shows no spike. Height maybe? Here comes the Ball Tracker. It shows that the ball was just clipping the top of middle. They retain the review but Marnus is a goner. No half ton for him here, first time it has happened for him in this Ashes. Australia in all sorts of trouble early on.
Fuller ball again, outside off, beats the outside edge again.
Another fullish ball, Head pushed it towards the off side.
Bumper this time. Head ducks under it. End of a superb over from Archer.
BEATEN! This is angled into the off pole, it pitches and straightens. Smith looks to defend but is beaten.
This is down the leg side, the batter looks to flick but misses.

FOUR OVERTHROWS! There was a run opportunity there. A direct hit would have been close. A short one which hurries onto Smith. He mistimes the pull towards square leg. Head wants a run and sets off. Smith takes a start and then sends him back. The fielder from mid-wicket gets to the ball and then throws it as he turns towards the non-striker's end. He misses. Archer fails to collect the ball as it bounces in front of him and it goes to the long off fence. England can't give away such free runs.
Outside off, this is left alone.
Another top nut! This is a brilliant spell by Broad. Shorter and around off, it straightens after pitching. Smith tries to defend but gets beaten.
A dot to end! Fuller and on middle, this is hit to mid on.
Good length ball on off, angled into the batter, Head taps it towards cover off the back foot.
FOUR! Crunched! Overpitched by Archer and Head lifts this over cover-point to get off the mark with a boundary. Archer won't mind this as the batter seems to be ready to drive the ball outside off.
Shortish length ball on middle, tucked towards the leg side for a couple this time.
Another shortish ball around off, Head looks to work it down the leg side but it goes off the outer half of the bat.
Edged but doesn't carry. Fuller ball, outside off, Head throws his bat at it to get an outside edge towards the slip cordon. It is wide of the diving slip fielder.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller ball on off. Head drives it straight to cover.
Shortish ball around off, Head looks to punch off the back foot but the ball goes off the toe end of the bat towards extra cover.

Good length ball on middle and leg, nips back further. Head looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. Broad appeals but nothing from the umpire. No review from England. A good call as the Ball Tracker rolled in to show that this was going down the leg side.
Good length around off, tapped towards point this time.
On the pads on a good length, Head nudges it fine down the leg side for a single.
FOUR! Smith is not bothered about what is happening around. Good length ball outside off, enough room for Smith to carve the cover drive for a boundary.
In the channel outside off, Head lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball around off again. Head looks to drive through covers but the ball takes the bottom edge and  goes towards Archer.
Shortish ball on middle, angled into the body. Head looks to work it down the leg side but is hit on the thigh pad.
Back of a length ball on the body this time, Head does well to fend it off towards the slip cordon.
FOUR! Top shot. Fullish length, there's room on offer for Head. He leans into the drive and powers it through covers for a boundary.

OUT! The middle stump takes a walk! What a jaffa from Archer! England are all over the visitors. Fuller length on middle, comes into the batter. Head looks to go for the drive but he has played all over this delivery. The ball sneaks through and shatters the timber behind. Wicket number two for Archer. Australia 240 ahead with 6 wickets in hand. Smith is watching all the damage from the other end.
Bumper but too high. Smith ducks under it.
Good length ball on middle, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball this time, Smith blocks by getting right behind the line of the ball.
Bumper again from Broad. But this goes down the leg side. Smith lets it go the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Smith.
Fuller around off this time, Smith blocks it towards mid-wicket.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards fine leg.
Bouncer this time outside off, Wade sways away from it.
Full length ball on middle and off, Wade pushes this towards cover-point.
Bouncer again! This time down the leg side and Wade ducks under it.

Fiery again! On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards fine leg for a single. Wade, when taking his single almost clashed with Archer. So Archer in return, while Wade took a start for the second, stood his ground which means he was right in front of Wade. The batter opts not to go around him, turns and goes back to his crease. There though wasn't two on there. Wade is off the mark with this single.
Way down the leg side by Archer, Smith goes after it and misses his flick.
Length ball around off, Wade shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball around off, Wade opens the face of his bat and guides this towards gully.
