Length ball around off, Wade looks to defend this off the back foot but gets beaten.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a couple. The fielder in the deep fumbled but no harm done.
Another one on the pads, Wade tucks this straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Last ball of the over, pushed to the man at cover.
This is angled into the pads, Smith works it wide of mid on for one. 600 runs for Smith in Ashes 2019 so far.
Shorter and outside off, it is left alone.
Two taken! Fuller and around off, Wade strokes it through covers and runs a brace.
Outside off, it is left alone.
This is angled into the middle pole, Wade gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Shorter in length and on the body, Wade ducks under it.
Length ball around off, Smith plays it off the back foot towards mid on.
Fuller one on the pads, Smith flicks it off his pads to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Fuller one outside off, Wade drives it towards covers and crosses over for a quick single.
Bouncer! Smith ducks under it.
Back of a length on the pads,  Smith hops and flicks it to fine leg and gets a couple.
Fuller length ball on middle and leg, Smith flicks it straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Wade paddles it down towards fine leg and gets couple.
Flighted delivery outside off, Wade sweeps it through square leg and gets a single.
Turn and bounce! Leach bowls one outside off and Smith dabs it to point.

Superb effort by Jofra in the outfield! Loopy delivery on the pads, Smith dances down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket. Jofra in the deep puts in a dive to pull the ball back. He does that but the ball continues to roll towards the fence. He leaps again to save a run as the batters take three.
Flatter one outside off, Wade flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off, Smith punches this towards mid off for a single.
Overton bowls on a length and outside off, Smith defends by coming right behind the line of the delivery.
Once again Smith is happy to defend this length ball outside off towards the off side.
Length and on middle, Smith flicks it off his pads towards fine leg for a single.
Good ball this from Overton. He bowls one on a length and outside off, But the ball climbs onto the batsmen and Wade at the last minute sways away from the line of the delivery.
Length and outside off, Wade lets it go through to the keeper.
This time Overton brings it a bit closer to the stumps and Wade just plays it to point. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
Floats it up on off, Smith drives it with the turn to covers. Roy makes a good stop diving to his right.

FOUR! Hammered! That is an aggressive shot from Smith. Australia going to go all guns blazing after the break? Maybe. Smith steps down the track and gets to the pitch of the ball and hammers it down to the long on fence.

Three now! Expects this one to be shorter and wider and it is like that. Smith stays right back and leg side of the ball, guides it down to third man for three. Overton chases the ball and pulls it back with a slide.

Flighted ball, it turns and bounces extra as Wade looks to work it down the leg side. But because of the turn and bounce he can't put bat on ball. It goes towards fine leg. Smith calls for a single but Wade is late in taking off. The fine leg fielder has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. A direct hit would've had Wade in trouble.
On middle, it is kept out.

In the air... but safe! Smith once again steps out but this time does not get to the pitch of it. He still goes ahead with the shot, ends up mistiming it over the mid off fielder for two. 10 from the first over after Tea.
On a length and on off, Wade drives it straight to the man at mid off.
Length ball and on off, Wade crouches low as he defends it onto the pitch.
Good length delivery outside off, Wade defends it off the outside half of his bat to gully.
BEATEN! Back of a length and outside off, Wade gets away from the line of the delivery to let it pass through.
Fuller one on off, Wade drives it to the man at mid off.
Wade defends this back of a length ball outside off to point.
Tossed up delivery on off, Smith plays it to point and gets off strike.
Flatter one on middle and leg, Wade defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on leg, Wade flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted on off, Smith works it to mid on and takes a single.
Tossed up on off, Wade looks to defend it to the off side but gets an inside edge on the pads.
Wade flicks this flighted one off his pads to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length and around off, Wade defends it to mid on.
Length ball and outside off, Wade  defends it to the off side.
Short on middle and Wade swivels to pulls it over mid-wicket but can't get his timing right. However, the ball goes towards deep mid-wicket and the batters take three in the meantime.
Smith works this length ball outside off towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length and outside off, Wade looks to run this down to third man but the fielder inside the circle cuts it off.
Wade defends this length ball outside off to point.
Smith defends this flatter one by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Tossed up and outside off, Smith gets down on one knee and sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Flatter one outside off, Smith drives it to long off and gets to the other end.
Wade defends this flighted one by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted on middle and leg, Wade looks to flick it off his pads but misses it.
Wade looks to work this flatter one towards the leg side but gets it off the inside half of his bat towards short fine leg.
On a length and on the pads, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.

FOUR! Beautifully done! Wade has played a gorgeous square cut. Overton bowls on a length and outside off, Wade frees his arms and cuts it through point for a magnificent boundary. That should give some confidence to Wade.
Wade defends this length ball outside off on the off side.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the backfoot.
Wade defends this length ball off his back foot.
BOUNCER! Overton goes short and Wade is spot on to sight that early and ducks under it.
Tossed up on leg pole, defended out.
This time it pitches outside leg and spins towards middle. Smith blocks it out.
Floated delivery outside the leg pole, Smith goes for the reverse sweep but misses.
Tossed up outside off, Smith opens the face of his bat awkwardly and guides this towards point to take a single.
This time Wade goes for the reverse sweep but even he misses it and is hit on the body.
Wade tried to sweep that one but missed it and was hit on the pads.

Lucky, very Lucky is Smith! Broad is on the money from the ball one of his new spell. He dishes a full ball which shapes back in. Smith looks to flick it but gets and inside edge which goes very close to the leg stump . He wanted a single but after seeing haring Bairstow from behind the wicket decided against it. Bairstow comes across and breaks the stumps but Smith was in anyway.
Smith defends this length ball  off the back foot.
FOUR! Fuller and on the pads, Smith flicks it awkwardly through mid-wicket for a boundary. His methods might be awkward but he is getting the desired result.
Good length ball on middle and off, Smith tries to push this towards the off side but gets an inside edge on it. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters take one.
Full length ball on off, pushed to mid on.
Length ball on middle and off, defended off the back foot by the batsman.
FOUR! Good improvisation by Smith. This is way down the leg side, Smith paddles this one very fine and the ball races through to the fine leg fence. 100 runs up for Australia in this innings.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Smith pushes it towards squarish mid-wicket and takes a single.
Wade sweeps this one but straight to the man at square leg.
Wade again tries to sweep but misses to get hit on the pad.
Wade has swept that one through the leg side. The batsmen have run through for a single.

DROPPED! Stokes is the culprit this time! This one is tossed up outside off, Smith goes for the reverse sweep and plays it uppishly. Stokes premeditates it and moves to his right from first slip before Smith had completed the shot. It went high and just towards the right of Stokes, he gets both his hands to it but the ball bursts through it. The ball rolls towards third man and the batters take a single. The main man for Australia survives and with this single, the lead for Australia has touched the 300-run mark.
FIFTY! Another one! A routine for this man. 26th Test half ton. Fuller ball around off, he taps it towards cover and takes off for a quick single to get to his milestone.
Good length ball outside off, tapped towards the off side.
Fuller one on the pads, Wade flicks it straight to the mid-on fielder.
Fuller ball outside off, directed towards gully this time by Wade.
Wide yorker this time. Wade looks to drive but he is late into the shot.
Fullish ball again, tapped towards point.
Smith goes for the reverse sweep off the first ball of the over but misses.
Again Smith brings out the reverse sweep. Stokes premeditates it and it is straight into his hands.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks this one towards square leg and takes a couple.
This time outside off, Smith guides this one towards backward point and takes a single.

NOT OUT! England lose a review! Tossed up outside off, Wade goes for the sweep and misses. The England players go up in appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Wade had signalled for the review even before the umpire denied England's appeal showing that it had not hit him anywhere on the glove or the bat. England however, think that it has hit him on the glove and they go for the review. The replays roll in and show that it has hit him on the forearm. The umpire wants to check for the LBW and thus the Ball Tracker comes in. The impact is outside off and Wade easily survives. No wonder he was as confident as it seemed even before the appeal was made.
The batsman dances down the track and they have run through for a single.
Good length ball on off, blocked comfortably.
Shortish ball on middle, Wade looks to heave this over the mid-wicket but the ball goes off the toe end of his bat. A single taken.
FOUR! Crunched through the covers! There is no stopping Steven Smith. Broad dishes a fuller ball outside off, Smith leans into his drive and creams this through the covers.
Good length ball, angled into the batter, blocked off the front foot this time.
Fuller ball on middle, blocked nicely this time towards the off side.
Good length around off, Smith taps it towards point for a single. He hared for the first run and wanted the second but Wade at the other end was ball watching.
FOUR! Length ball just outside off, Smith gets onto the back foot and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Smith seems to be playing with the bowler's mind here. Archer bowls this length ball closer to the body expecting that Smith would shuffle across the stumps. Instead, he makes room and guides this past the third slip fielder for a boundary towards third man.
Bouncer by Archer to Smith, he initially looks to play at it but leaves it in the end.
Another bouncer, Smith ducks under it.
Smith plays another one awkwardly. This time it is a slower bouncer, Smith crouches and plays it at the last moment back towards Archer.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards the leg side.
Wade pushes this fuller one towards mid on.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Full and wide outside off, Smith drives this powerfully towards cover but straight to the man.
FOUR! Good length ball on middle and leg, Smith slaps this over Mid on and gets a boundary off it. He didn't time it that well and that's why it went to the long on fence on the bounce.
Smith punches this towards point off the back foot and takes a single.
Shorter in length this time, Wade pulls this through square leg and takes a couple.
Short of a length by Archer, Smith blocks it awkwardly towards short leg.
Another bouncer, this time way outside off. Smith goes towards the ball and then ducks under it.
Another bouncer over middle and leg, Smith ducks under it.
Another bouncer by Archer, Smith goes towards the ball and again leaves it at the last moment.
Short of a length, Smith cuts it towards point and takes a single.
Wide outside off, Wade guides it to third man.
Smith moves way down the leg side to play at that and pushes it towards mid on.n.

FOUR! Pulled away handsomely! Smith is looking from another planet right now. Short of a length and outside off, Smith pulls this wide of mid-wicket for a boundary. Root inside the circle dives to his right but cannot save the boundary.
FIVE WIDES! Bad ball from Broad or mind games from Smith? Well, only Broad would know! He bowls it way down the leg side and it has evaded Bairstow to crash into the fine leg fence.
On the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
On the pads of Wade, he flicks it but straight to the man.
Fullish ball on off, Wade pushes this down the ground. Broad gets his hand on that as the ball goes to mid off and the batters take one.

FOUR! Smith brings up the 100-run stand up between him and Wade. Another short of a length ball by Broad, Smith rocks onto the back foot and pulls this one towards long on for a boundary. Smith moves to 81 with this boundary. Another century on the cards? Most probably!
Good length ball on the off pole. Wade blocks it out.
Full and wide outside off, Wade pushes this towards cover and takes a single.
Bouncer by Archer and Smith is on the ground in an attempt to evade it. Even though he is on the ground, he does not stop practicing his strokes as he is shadowing how to play the upper cut.
On the leg pole line by Archer, Smith shuffles and tries to flick but misses as the ball goes over the leg pole.
Good yorker by Archer, on the pads of Smith, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Bouncer to Wade but he does well to evade it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Smith is out of here after setting Australia well on their way! One can say that this was a suicidal shot but Smith wanted to up the ante of the game. Leach tosses it up way outside off, Smith comes down the track in an attempt to go over the man at long off. He does not get to the pitch of the ball and does not get the best connection on it. Stokes runs to his left from long off and takes an easy catch in the deep. The crowd breathe a huge sigh of relief as the main man is out of here.
Wade dances down the track to punch it through mid on for a single to this loopy full ball.
Flighted ball around off, Paine pushes this back to the bowler.
Short ball outside off, turns further away. Paine drives this through cover-point to get off the mark with the single.
Flatter ball, turning into the batter this time, Wade goes back and punches it through covers to get a couple.
FOUR! Fuller ball this time. Wade leans into the drive and carves this through the covers to get another boundary.
Fuller ball around off, Paine drives it towards cover and takes off for the run. Roy at covers dives to his right and has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. Paine had made his ground though.

OUT! A stunner from Bairstow behind the wicket to send Wade packing. Fullish ball outside off, shaping away. Wade is looking for quick runs and hence he throws his bat at the ball. He can only manage an outside edge which goes to the left of Bairstow. He dives to his left and holds onto it with one hand. A handy knock from Wade comes to an end. However, no declaration from Australia.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Starc.

This time on a good length, Starc goes for the drive and edges it. The ball goes between third slip and gully. The man in the deep stops it and the batters take one. Starc is off the mark with this one.
Paine looks to defend off the back foot but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Outside off, Paine looks to drive but misses.

Spin for Leach but missed by Starc and Bairstow too. He pitches this one outside off and gets it to spin in to the southpaw. He misses the line of the delivery and so does Bairstow as it goes through him towards fine leg and the batters take one. The ball also misses the stumps by a whisker.
FOUR! Floated on middle and off, Paine lofts this one over mid on and past the long on fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Another boundary! This is shortish and outside off, Paine goes onto the back foot and slaps it through extra cover for a boundary.
That ball has taken the inside edge of Paine's bat and thudded into his pads.
Paine defends this tossed up delivery back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Reverse swept by Paine and this time he connects it properly as the ball races towards the third man fence.
This is on the pads, Starc works it on the leg side for one.
Fuller and on off, Paine pushes it to mid off.
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman.
Shorter and on middle, Paine mistimes his pull to mid on.
FOUR! Dealing in boundaries is Paine. This is short and on middle, Paine goes back and pulls it nicely through mid-wicket. It is a well-controlled pull shot.
One more short one on middle, it is ducked under.
Easy run as Starc opens the face of the bat and guides it through covers.
A couple now! Paine slaps this towards cover. Roy dives to his left, gets a hand to it, can't stop two though.
Just over and another two! Shorter and on middle, Paine comes down the track. He once again mistimes the stroke. It goes over the outstretched hand of Roy at covers.
WIDE! Way too wide outside off, it is left alone.

NOT OUT! There was a huge gap between bat and ball. Not sure why the review was taken. A short one down the leg side, Paine looks to pull but misses. Bairstow appeals but the umpire shakes his head. Root reviews at the end but replays show nothing. Also, this ball has been wided by the umpire as it is too high.
A single now as Paine pulls it through square leg for one.
On the pads of Starc, he tries to flick this one but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball rolls towards the leg side and the batters take one.
Shorter in length and on off, Burns guides it to point.
On the shorter side again, it is defended.

OUT! In the air... taken! Could Australia have asked for a better start than this? The ploy to start the bowling with Pat Cummins has worked wonders. Also, it is a big wicket as Burns has been the in-form player for the hosts. This is a soft, soft dismissal. It is a nothing delivery, down the leg side. Burns looks to flick but is early into the shot. A leading edge and it lobs towards Head at extra cover.

OUT! TIMBER! That is a peach! This is Pat Cummins, this is Australia at their best. Outstanding start for them! Root bags a first-baller. An absolute beauty! Exactly what a pace bowler is taught - to hit the top of off and Cummins has done that here. He lands this one on a length and around middle, it pitches and straightens. Root is squared up as he tries to defend. The ball goes past the outside edge and hits the off pole. Root can't believe it as he looks back once. He would probably be thinking, that why him? Why did he get such a perfect delivery first up. Pin-drop silence here. A slow walk towards the pavilion as he knows his side is in big, big trouble now.
Good length and on middle, it is kept out nicely.

One more length ball around off, Roy pushes it to mid on. End of a tremendous over. What a start by Cummins. England get no closer to the target they were set to achieve while Australia get a fist of the wickets they needed
Starts with a length ball, closer to the off pole, Denly is right behind the line of the ball to block towards the off side.
Same line and length as the last ball, Denly again solid in defense.
Good leave that one. Another good length ball but this is in the channel. Denly covers his stumps to let it go to the keeper.
Oops! Shortish ball, Denly goes to block but it rises a bit to hit on the gloves and then on the elbow. Lucky that it didn't went onto the stumps.
Beaten this time! Another ball in the channel outside off. Denly can't resist this time and has a poke. The ball goes past the outside edge.
Fullish ball this time, tapped towards covers this time by Deny. Top over from Hazlewood to compliment the wicket maiden from Cummins.
Another good delivery! This is angled into the batter from wide of the crease. It is on a length, pitches and straightens. Roy looks to defend but then drags his bat back.
England are underway! This is on the pads, Roy works it through square leg for two.
On middle and on a length. Roy gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Roy is really watching the ball closely here. This is shorter and on off, Roy goes back and keeps it out solidly.
A crisp drive! Fuller and on off, Roy strokes it nicely but to mid off.

FOUR! First boundary of the chase! This is easy for Roy. A half volley on the pads, it is worked through mid-wicket and the ball races away. Maybe Cummins was guilty of trying a little too hard and hence, ends up bowling a boundary delivery.
On the fuller side, no swing on offer for the bowler. Denly plants his front foot forward and strokes it to mid off.
A little too straight, Denly works it behind square on the leg side for two.
A little too straight once again, Denly tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Corrects his line and bowls it outside off, it is left alone.
One more ball on a good length and around off, it is guided towards point.
Short and on middle, Denly ducks under it.
A little too short this time, Roy stands tall and pushes it to mid off.
Good work from Wade! This is on middle, Roy looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards short leg where Wade shows good reflexes and stops it.
Outside off, it is left alone.
One more ball outside off, Roy lets it be.
This is angled into the pads, Roy gets it past short leg this time and takes an easy two.
A dot to end! This is on middle again, Roy works it to mid-wicket.
On off, Denly works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! That is a top shot. Minimal risk as it was with the turn and it was nicely hit. Stretches out and plays the sweep shot. Drags it outside off and hits it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On middle, it is kept out.

OHHH! That was close! Picked the wrong ball to sweep there. This is tossed up outside off, it is too full. Denly looks to sweep again but misses. It just misses the off pole. The positive approach is right but you need to pick the right balls.
On middle, this is worked to mid on.
A single as this is worked through square leg.
Fuller ball on off, pushed towards point by Denly.
Fuller again but too wide to make Denly play at it. He doesn't wanna chase these at this moment in time.
Another fuller ball, again wide outside off. No swing on offer for him. Denly watches it go back to the keeper again. A bumper now?
Nah. Dishes out a yorker does Starc. This swung in the air. Denly does well to bring his bat down and jam it away.

He looks for another yorker but this one is not the perfect one. It is a overpitched ball, Denly leans into the drive to cream it through. However, it doesn't have the legs to reach the fence. They take three before the cover fielder chase and return the ball. 1 more ball to go. Can Starc do something?
No he can not as he bowls a wasteful of a delivery. He goes for the bumper but bowls it way down the leg side. Roy lets it go to the keeper. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4.
Starts off with a full ball and on middle, Denly pushes it to mid on. A huge cheer for him as he played it nicely. That is how it is going to be today, England fans will be right behind their team.
Gets it right this time and bowls it outside off, it tails back in but not enough to make the batter play.

A loud appeal but that seems to be going down leg! Once again Hazlewood gets it to tail back in, this time it is fuller but a touch straighter. Denly looks to drive but misses to get hit on the pads. Ball Tracker confirms it is going down leg.
One more good ball! Just outside off and it is shorter. Denly leaves it nicely.
On the middle pole, Denly gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off this time. Denly watches it shape in and go to the keeper. A tight start from Hazlewood first up.
On a length and around off, Roy keeps it out.
That is a beauty! This is angled into the batter from wide of the crease which means Roy has to play at it. The ball straightens and beats the outside edge of the bat.
In the air but wide! FOUR! First boundary and runs of Day 5.  This is angled into the pads, Roy flicks it uppishly but wide of the diving mid-wicket fielder and bags a boundary.
Goes back to bowling length on off, Roy gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Outside off, this is left alone.
A length delivery to end on middle, Roy pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball closer to the off pole. Denly lunges forward and blocks.
Beaten! A muted appeal follows but dies down quickly. A peach from Hazlewood. Good length in the channel outside off, the ball shapes away from the push of Denly to beat the outside edge.
Good length ball again on off, blocked nicely this time.
Another ball in the channel on a good length, this time Denly lets it go to the keeper.
Hezlewood continues bowling the perfect line and length to the right-hander. This is closer to Denly's off pole. He taps it towards cover and takes off for a quick run. First run for him.
Fuller ball on off for Roy. He pushes it back to the bowler.
Just short! Pushing at a delivery Denly need not do. This is behind a length and outside off, Denly looks to stroke it on the up but then stops midway. He ends up chipping it just short of mid off.

Another loud appeal and a long one but nothing from the umpire! This is on middle and it jags back in. Denly fails to put bat on ball and is hit on the front pad. An appeal but not given. Paine signals it is going down leg.
On the fuller side and on middle, Denly strokes it nicely to mid on.
Goes back to bowling length on off, it is blocked solidly.
One more length ball on off, Denly is solid in defense.
Another solid push! On off, Denly pushes it towards covers but for no runs.
Back of a length and it is coming back in. Roy defends it onto the ground.
A little too straight, Roy fails to put bat on ball and gets hit high on the pads.
Outside off, Roy watches the ball nicely and lets it be.
Shorter again, it comes slow off the surface. Roy gets right behind the line and defends it.
On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
A short one, Denly spots it early and ducks under it.
Length ball on off, blocked by Roy easily.
Beaten with a beauty! On a length and jags back in. Roy looks to push with hard hands but the ball sneaks in between bat and pad. Wasn't too high from the stumps either.
Bumper this time but this one goes down the leg side. Roy ducks under it.
Fuller ball on middle, Roy pushes this towards mid on and takes a run.
Back of a length ball this time. Denly ducks under it.
A solid block from Denly to finish the over. A good length ball on off from Hazlewood. Denly gets behind the line and blocks it towards the off side.
One more ball on a length and on off, Roy pushes it to mid off.
On off, it is kept out again. This is a good start for England, both the batters are looking solid.
Down the leg side, Roy looks to flick but misses.
Almost! Just as a write that, Roy plays one out awkwardly. This comes back in after landing on off, Roy looks to put bat on ball but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
This is on middle, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
On middle, the batter pushes it to mid on.
Starts with a fuller ball on the pads, Roy flicks it towards square leg for a run.
On the pads, Denly looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Gets it right this time and lands it on off and on a length. Denly keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! EDGY! Lucky there was Denly. Not a good shot that. Denly is sucked into going after a wide delivery outside off. The ball flies off the outside edge over third slip. Marnus Labuschagne does not react in time and it goes over him and to the third man fence. That went really quickly.
A single to end! Denly pushes this towards cover and gets to the other end.
Flighted outside off, Denly pads it away.
Another tossed up ball outside off, Denly lunges to defend but the ball turns back in, it goes off the inside edge and onto the pads and lobs safe on the off side.
FOUR! That is a top sweep shot. A shot which Denly looks really confident while playing. He drags it from outside off and gets it through square leg.
Loopy ball on off, it is worked with the turn to mid on.
One more sweep shot, this time to the fielder at deep mid-wicket so just a run.
A tossed up ball on off to end, Denly defends it out.
Good ball and equally well played. Starc is targeting the stumps. He looks to bowl a yorker but dishes out a full toss on middle. Denly blocks solidly.
Outside off this time, Denly lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off again. Denly has room to slash this through point but he mistimes the shot towards gully.
On the pads this time, Denly tucks it towards fine leg off the back foot to take a run.

FOUR! That's done nicely by Roy. Another attempt of bowling the yorker has gone wrong as Starc sends a full toss on the pads. Roy whips it firmly through the diving mid on fielder. The fielder gets up and chases but the ball wins the race.
On a length, closer to off pole, Roy looks to block but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards mid on.
Nice use of the feet from Denly and works it with the turn through mid-wicket for one.
Shorter and outside off, it turns back in. Roy works it with soft hands towards the leg side.

In the air... safe! Heart in the mouth moment for Roy there. This is floated up outside off, it turns back in sharply. Roy looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It lobs over short leg and towards mid-wicket for one.
Quicker and on off, it is blocked.

Just short now! Once again a heart in the mouth moment, this time for Denly. He brings out the sweep again but hits it uppishly towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder there runs in and then slides to take it but the ball lands short of him. Good stop in the end, saves three.
Very full outside off, Roy opens the face and guides it to point. An action-packed over by lyon comes to an end.

OHHH! Australia making things happen now. A short one by Starc on the body. Denly may have been expecting a full one. He tries to fend it awkwardly but it goes off the handle and lands safe on the off side.
A solid drive but for no runs! Fuller and outside off, Denly hits it hard but to covers.
Shortens his length a little and lands on middle, defended.
On the fuller side and outside off, Denly goes after it again but finds cover.
Gets one in the gap! Not right off the middle but enough to get three. Shorter and outside off, Denly slaps it through covers and takes one short of four.
Good running! This is on middle, Roy taps it towards mid on and takes one quickly.
Extremely full outside off, Roy pushes it to mid off.
Very wide outside off, it is a full toss. Roy drives it square to point.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.

Nicely played! 50 up for England a loud cheer by the crowd. The 50-run stand is also up, a vital one as England were 0 for 2 when the two joined association. Need to keep going. Roy pushes this nicely through covers and takes two.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On off, Roy gets behind the line and keeps it out.
Shortish length on the body from round the wicket. Denly taps it towards mid on for a quick run.
Length ball around off, Roy walks across, blocked.
FOUR! Crunched through covers. Starc overpitches outside off, Roy leans into the drive and creams it through covers.
Squared up on that one. Starc pitches this on off and makes it jag away from Roy's defense and beat the outside edge.
Bowls this one on a slightly fullish length on middle. Roy is solid in defense this time.
Another fuller ball. Roy pushes it towards cover.
Floated fuller ball on middle, pushed towards mid on for a single by Denly.
Another fuller ball which lands on the rough and bounces high into the mitts of Paine.
Another loopy ball on off, Roy blocks it nicely this time.

And another one lands on the rough outside off and keeps low. Roy looks to block but misses to get hit on the back pad. Lyon appeals but nothing from the umpire. The Ball Tracker rolls in and confirms that the umpire was right. The impact was outside off and was clipping the stumps which means it would've been umpire's call on hitting the wicket. A good call from the umpire.
Floated ball on middle this time, Roy comes down the track to work it towards mid on for a run.
On the pads, guided towards fine leg by Denly.
Lands it just outside off, Roy shoulders arms to this one.
Closer to the off pole this time, Roy pushes it to covers.
Another one on a length and outside off, Roy pushes it to covers.
Another one on a length and outside off, it is left alone.
That was close! A yorker just outside off, Roy is late in bringing his bat down and the ball just about kisses the off pole.
Good fielding! This is fuller and on off, Roy strokes it towards mid off. Cummins runs to his right and dives to push it to his right. Mid on then does the mopping up job. The batters take two.
Denly comes down the pitch, he does not get to the pitch of the ball so defends it.
Uses his feet again but once again does not get to the pitch of it. Looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An ambitious appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire.
Another tossed up ball on off, Denly keeps it out.
Shorter and on off, Denly whips it with the turn through mid-wicket for two.
Another loud shot but nothing! This is floated outside off, Denly pads it away with his bat behind the pad. An appeal but the umpire feels a shot is offered and he shakes his head.

Overthrows! Denly uses his feet and hits it to the right of Cummins at mid on. The batters take a quick run. Cummins fires it at the keeper's end but it is a wild one. No one backing up and hence, the fielder from slip hares after it and saves a run for his side.
Fuller ball outside off to start with. Denly finds extra cover fielder to his firm drive.
Good leave this form Denly. He trusts the length of the ball there. Pitched around off, comes into the batter who shoulders arms and sees the ball go over the timbers.
Fuller ball on the pads, Denly looks to flick but is hit on the pads.
Fuller ball around off, Denly goes for a drive this time but gets an inside edge the ball goes towards fine leg. He gets a run.
In the channel outside off, left alone by Roy this time.

OUT! KABOOM! There's the breakthrough Australia needed. Cummins has provided it. They had to wait for quite a while today for the first wicket but they have now got it. Australia will hope this opens the floodgates. Once again we see the ball sneaking through Roy's bat and pad. Cummins bowls it just outside off and on a length. Roy lunges and tries to push at it but leaves a gap between bat and pad. The ball tails back in, goes between the gap and hits the stumps behind. Also, credit to Paine for the last minute change. Starc was ready to bowl but in the end, he got Cummins on and that has worked wonders. Roy walks back after getting off to a start.
Shorter one around off, this kept low. Pushed towards bowler.

Dropped! A chance goes begging there! A beauty from Lyon as he pitches this again on rough. Denly looks to block but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball lobs high towards Paine's right who can't hold on. It goes towards fine leg for a run eventually.
The batsman works it down the leg side. One run added to the total.
On off and kept low. Stokes does well to block it towards the off side.
Another one around off, Stokes blocks it off the back foot.
Flighted ball on middle, blocked off the front foot this time.
Ouch! Another good ball. This ball is shaping in nastily. It comes back from outside off and that too after landing. Denly fails to put bat and ball and is hit near the box.
Good length again and on off, Denly pushes it to mid off.
Goes extremely full and it is tailing back in from outside off. Denly jams it out.
Changes it up now and bangs it short on the body, Denly ducks under it.

LUCKY FOUR! This is just outside off, Denly is not sure whether to play at it or leave it. In the end he tries to leave but the ball hits the bat which is at an angle. Goes past the diving third slip fielder and into the third man fence.
Nicely guided! This is just outside off, Denly opens the face of the bat and guides it through backward point for two.
Floats it up on middle, Stokes keeps it out.
On middle, Stokes gets right behind the line and defends it again.
Sharp turn and bounce! Flatter and outside off, the ball pitches, spins away and also bounces. Stokes looks to defend but is beaten.
Quicker and on middle, Stokes blocks it easily.
On the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, this time, Stokes gets behind the line of the ball and blunts it onto the pitch.
Outside off, it is left alone.
BEATEN! Cummins goes wide of the crease and angles it just outside off. Denly plays inside the line and gets beaten.
Shorter and on off, Joe pushes it to mid off.
This is angled into the batter, Denly goes right back and keeps it out.
Shortish and outside off, Denly looks to punch it through covers but is early in the shot. It goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Denly drives it to mid off.
On middle, blocked.
Almost! Stokes misread the length there. He goes back to a delivery which he should be forward too. gets his bat down though and keeps it out.
Loopy ball and on off, Stokes pushes it to mid off.
That must have hurt! Shorter and on off, Stokes goes back and pushes it but the ball hits the man at silly point.
On middle, it is kept out.
A single to end the over! This is on the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
Shorter and around middle, it is angled away. Stokes leaves it alone.

OUT! Stokes walks! He is caught behind! This is a massive, massive wicket. Probably the biggest of them all as Stokes has been the man for England. Excellent sportsmanship by him though. Not many in modern day cricket walk but he does here and that too in a game which means so much. Brilliant. Brilliant by Cummins too. He is once again the man doing it for Australia. This is shortish and on off, Stokes initially looks to defend but then tries to leave it on length. Too late by then though as the ball hits the bottom part of the inside edge and goes to the right of Paine. He takes it with a dive and appeals, it is a very confident one. The umpire is unmoved but what do we see? Stokes walks. Australia are ecstatic. England in trouble now. Australia just 6 wickets away. They would hope to take another before Lunch. A rare failure for Stokes.
Back of a length and on off, this is kept out.

FOUR LEG BYES! This is on off again and it jags back in. Bairstow looks to defend but the ball hits the higher part of the back pad and goes between first slip and the keeper and down to the third man fence. There is an appeal from the players but nothing from the umpire.
On the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
End of a successful over. On off, it is kept out.
On middle stump on a good length, Denly whips it firmly through mid-wicket for a couple.
In the channel this time, Denly covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Good length on off, tapped towards gully this time.

Beaten! What a jaffa! Huge appeal as well but not given. Hazlewood pitches this around off, it tails back in to beat Denly's bat and go to Pant behind the wicket. They appeal but not given. Australia do not take the review. The Ball Tracker arrives to and shows that the impact was umpire's call. No inside edge either so can't be caught behind. A good decision from the umpire.
FOUR! Fuller ball on off, driven through covers nicely for a boundary. Denly moves to 48 with that one.
Bumper to end the over. Denly sways away from it.
Back of a length on off, Bairstow guides it to point.
A short one on middle, JB ducks under it.
Outside off, it is left alone.
On middle, it is pushed to mid on. It is a NO BALL as Cummins has overstepped.
Shortish and on off, Jonny punches it to covers.
Bairstow is off the mark! He works it behind square and collects two.
An away swinger outside off, it is left alone.
Almost another one! This is on a length and around off, it stays very low. Denly gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
One more length ball on middle, Denly defends it off the back foot.
That came back in a long way again! This lands outside off and jags back in. The length is shorter. Denly misses his shot and gets hit high on the thigh pad.
On middle, Denly pushes it to mid on.
Nicely left! Just outside off, Denly shuffles across and shoulders arms to this one.
Denly survives but by just! Hazlewood lands this just outside off, it is bowled from wide of the crease so Denly plays at it. He is beaten as he does inside the line. LUNCH ON DAY 5!
Good start for Cummins! On a length and around off, it comes back in. JB looks to defend but misses to get hit near the stomach.
Goes very full and on middle, it is hit down to mid on.
Another good ball! This is on off and it comes back in again. Bairstow looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Very full around off, Bairstow strokes it to mid off.
Outside off, the batter does not play at it.
One more ball outside off, it is left alone. A maiden to begin with by Cummins.
On middle and turning away. Denly looks to flick but misses.
Denly comes down the track and works it to short fine leg for no runs.
Very full on off, it is worked to mid on.
On middle and it is too short. Denly works it through square leg for one.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
A little too straight again, Bairstow clips it to short leg.
Fullish and on off, Denly strokes it to mid off.

FOUR! Fifty for Denly! Excellent innings from him. He gets there with a delightful stroke. He creams this full delivery on off through mid off and it races away. He needs to make it big here, he just can't relax. It is his third in Tests.
Back of a length on off, it is guided to point.
Shorter and on the body, does not bounce a lot. Denly looks to duck but is hit on the body.
OHHH! Back of a length and on off, Denly looks to play it late but gets a bottom edge onto the pads.
Good nut to end! Just outside off, Denly is not sure whether to play at it or not. He tries to leave it in the end but it goes off the bottom part towards gully.
Floated around off, pushed towards point by Jonny.
Fuller around off. Lyon aiming to rough outside off of the batsman. But this is too wide.
Goes full and straight this time, blocked easily.
Flatter one on off this time, another solid block from Bairstow.

Just short of the short leg fielder. That shoot off the surface after pitching. Bairstow wanted to work it fine down the leg side but extra bounce means he tries to fend off towards the leg side. It lobs but falls just short of Marnus Labuschagne at short leg.
On the pads this time, nudged towards fine leg by Jonny.
Fuller and on middle, it is hit back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on off, Joe defends it out.
One more back of a length ball on middle, Denly stays back and keeps it out.
A sharp bumper, Denly ducks under it.
One more short ball on middle, Denly ducks under it again.
OHHH! One more length ball around off, this one pitches and comes back in. Denly looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle, it is worked through square leg for one.

OUT! Finally, finally, Nathan Lyon gets a wicket. It is of the well set Denly and England now have half the side back in the hut. Denly once again falls shortly after getting to his half ton. This is an excellent delivery though. Turn, bounce, it had everything. It lands outside off and spins back in sharply. There is a lot of bounce on it. Denly goes back and tries to defend but the ball hits the handle and lobs towards short leg where Labuschagne takes a dolly. Early wicket for Australia after the break. Also, the visitors will hope, that wicket works wonders for Lyon.
Good follow-up delivery after the wicket ball. This is floated outside off, it turns back in sharply. Buttler lets it be.
Good ball again! Flatter and outside off, this one too turns back in. Buttler looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Very full this time, Buttler strokes it to mid on.
Flighted ball outside off, it turns back in. Buttler tries to defend but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one. He is off the mark.
Good length ball angled into the batter, Buttler hops and pushes it towards mid on.
EDGY FOUR! Goes slightly fuller around off, Buttler looks to push it towards the off side but the ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of the slip cordon to the third man fence.
Shortish ball outside off this time, Buttler shoulders arms.
On the pads this time, clipped towards square leg for a couple. It brings 100 up for England and it gets huge cheer from the English supporters.
FOUR BYES! Bumper but too high as Buttler ducks. Even Paine can't do much as it flies over him towards the fine leg fence.
Beaten! A superb nut to finish the over. Pitched on middle on a length and shapes away to go past the outside edge.
Flatter and quicker on the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
This is flatter again outside off, it turns back in. Buttler goes back and tries to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Very full and on off, Buttler strokes it to mid off.
Down the leg side, Buttler lets it be.
Another one which lands outside off and turns back in. Buttler looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Down the leg side, it is left alone.
Shorter in length and around off, Bairstow guides it behind point and takes two.
A little too straight this time from wide of the crease. Jonny nudges it through backward square leg and gets to the other end.
Good length delivery outside off, Buttler does not play at it.
That kept a bit low! On middle and it stays a touch low. Buttler looks to defend but it goes off the bottom part towards mid-wicket.
Slightly fuller this time and it shapes back in. Buttler looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards mid on.
Another length ball on off to end the over. Buttler goes back and keeps it out.
On middle, Bairstow works it with the turn through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Nicely played! This is floated up outside off, Buttler gets his front leg to the pitch of the ball and then strokes it through covers for three. Just a mere push there.
A single now as Jonny works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
One more single! This time Buttler goes right back and works it behind square for one.
Changes the angle and bowls it from around the wicket. It is down the leg side, Paine fails to collect it and it goes down towards fine leg. A bye is taken.
This lands on off but then turns back in. Buttler works it around the corner for one.
Shortish ball on middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Good length ball which is angled into the batter, Buttler blocks it well.
Another one angled into the batter. Another solid block from Buttler.
Good leave that one as Buttler trusted the length. The ball pitches outside off and comes back in sharply. Buttler shoulders arms and watches it go over the stumps.
Fuller ball this time, negotiated easily by Buttler.
Fuller ball but outside off, Buttler doesn't play at it.
Flatter and outside off, it spins back in again. Bairstow goes back and tries to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
On off, Bairstow goes back and keeps it out.
Outside off, JB looks to play it late, it goes off the outer half towards short third man for one.
Very full outside off, Buttler defends it out.
On middle, Buttler works it to short fine leg for no runs.
Floats it up and on off, Buttler goes back and keeps it onto the ground. He went back to a pretty full delivery there but that is how he has been playing Lyon throughout the series.
Back of a length on off, Jonny stands tall and pushes it to covers.
One more on a length and around off, Bairstow goes back and keeps it out.
Attacks the stumps once again, Bairstow is solid in defense.
This starts on off and it comes back in. Bairstow looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards square leg.
A little too straight, it is worked wide of mid on for one.
One more ball outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
Quicker and on off, Bairstow flicks but can't get past short leg.
FOUR! Too full and it is put away! Full and on off, Bairstow leans into it and strokes it down to the long off fence.
Flatter and on off, Jonny defends it out.
Very full and on middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Lovely use of the wrists! Also, there is minimal risk in that shot as it was with the turn. On middle and it is fuller. Buttler whips it through mid-wicket and the ball races away to the fence.
Another one which is very full, Buttler flicks it to mid on. 9 from the over.
Starts off with a short ball so does not give the ball much time to do its bit. Bairstow ducks under it.
Goes fuller this time but no swing visible. It is outside off, left alone.
Shorter but down the leg side, Bairstow looks to flick but misses. Paine dives to his left and takes it nicely.
Better! This is angled into the stumps, JB keeps it out. Starc not getting the ball to do a lot till now.
Shorter in length and on middle, Bairstow stands tall and pushes it to mid on.
Three to end the over! Easy for Bairstow. It is full and on the pads, Bairstow works it through mid-wicket. The sweeper runs to his left and stops it. Three taken.
Flatter and on off, Bairstow guides it through point and gets to the other end.
Big turn there! Tosses this one up outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it as it turns away.
Shorter again and on off, Buttler pushes it through covers for one.
Another one which is a touch short. Bairstow this time goes back and pushes it through covers for one.
Good line and length! It is landed on middle, it turns away. Buttler gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
A good nut to end! On middle, Buttler defends it outside the line. It goes off the inner half to the right of the bowler. Two good deliveries to end by ML.
A little too short and a little too straight, Bairstow works it through mid-wicket for one.
Way too wide outside off, the batter need not play at those.
Short again, Buttler easily goes back and keeps it out.
Slightly fuller than the last ball. Buttler pushes it to covers.
Too short! Buttler guides it to point. Starc has been a touch short in this spell. He needs to get it up there.
Better! This is on a length and around off, Buttler is solid in defense.
Slower through the air outside off, Bairstow goes back and pushes it back to the bowler.
A little too straight, it is worked to the fielder at short fine leg.
Loopy ball on off, JB flicks it with the turn to the leg side.
One more ball to which JB goes back and works it to short fine leg.
This is given a lot more air and the length is fuller around off. Bairstow defends it, off the front foot.
This is wider outside off, it turns back in but not enough to make the batter play.
A full toss but Buttler misses out. He smashes it but straight back to the bowler.
On middle. JB keeps it out.
Flatter and outside off, Buttler lets it be.
Loopy ball around the pads, it is worked to the man at mid on.
A little too short, Buttler works it behind square on the leg side for one. These two are going along well here. Actually, it was an inside edge onto the pads and not right off the middle.

Misfield! Labuschagne comes from around the wicket to land it in the rough. He ends up bowling a full toss which Jonny works it through mid-wicket. Head in the deep gets to the ball but misfields and an extra run is taken. Three in total.

OUT! LBW! Jonny Bairstow has to walk back. Starc strikes first ball after Drinks. How often do we see a wicket after the break! Beauty from him to wrap him in front of the stumps. Height was the only issue which could've had saved him but no, the Ball Tracker rolls in to show that the the ball is clipping the stumps.  It was pitched on a good length and came back in sharply. Bairstow wanted to work it down the leg side but was hit flush on the pads. A huge appeal follows and umpire Dharmasena agrees with the Aussies. Bairstow though sends it upstairs after having a look at Buttler at the non-striker's end but he has to walk back. Second time Starc gets him in his Test and the 8th overall - most by any bowler against Jonny.
That was on target as well. Full and just around off, stays low a touch, Overton gets down to keep it out.

This is edged but played with soft hands. Hence, goes down to ground. Full and outside off, swinging away, Craig looks to drive but the ball goes off the outside edge, onto the ground and towards second slip who misfields and allows a single.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Around off, defended back to the bowler.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Floats it up on off, it is kept out.
Another one is worked to the mid-wicket region.
Flatter and outside off, Overton goes back and keeps it out.
Nicely bowled! This is slower and it is  tossed up outside off, Overton lunges and tries to defend but it goes off the inner half wide of short leg.
A shorter delivery to end on middle, Overton works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, it is left alone.
One more delivery outside off, Buttler does not fiddle with it.
A yorker outside off, Buttler jams it out to point.
A couple! Fuller and on off, Buttler strokes it through cover-point for two.
Well bowled! This is on a length and around middle, stays a touch low. Buttler does well to keep it out.
A leave to end as Starc bowls it outside off.
This is fuller and on off, it tails back in. Overton gets his front leg out of the way and works it down to fine leg for one.
On the fuller side on off, Buttler punches it past the bowler. Bancroft the sub at mid off dives to his right and makes a good stop.
Good length and outside off, it is left alone.
This is angled into the stumps, Jos defends it back towards the bowler.
Crisp drive! Very full and on off, Jos creams it but to mid off.
A length ball outside off to end. Buttler lets it go. This is really been a watchful innings by Buttler.
Shorter and on middle, Overton works it through square leg and gets Buttler on strike.
Flatter and on off, Buttler goes right back and works it with the turn towards backward square leg for one.
That lobs to short leg but it is off the pads. It lands around off and then turns back in. Overton looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Quicker and on middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
That stayed low but nicely played! This is on off, it stays very low. Buttler gets his bat down in time and works it through square leg for one.
A huge appeal but not given! This is floated up outside off, it turns back in. Overton gets his pad out of the line of off and tries to defend but misses to get hit on it.
That is unplayable! That went away like a leg spinner. It is on a length and around off, it pitches and moves away sharply. Buttler tries to defend but is beaten, by a long way though.
Shorter and on off, Buttler looks to defend at first but then tries to bail out. Too late as it goes off the bottom half but on the bounce to the third slip fielder.
BEATEN! Another top nut. The changed ball is really talking. This starts on off, pitches and then moves away. Jos tries to block it but gets beaten.
Gets this one back in now but it is a touch shorter. Buttler leaves it on length.

That is another lovely nut! Whizzes past the outside edge again. Cummins goes wide of the crease and angles it into the batter. Buttler is drawn into a defensive stroke. The ball though shapes away and goes past the outside edge.

And again! One more ball on a length and around off, it straightens after pitching. Whizzes past the outside edge as Buttler tries to defend. End of an outstanding over. The important thing is, Buttler survives and also, not a lot he could with those deliveries. Just needs to get it out of his mind.
Fuller one on middle, pushed back to the bowler by Overton.
Fuller again on off, pushed towards the off side.
Shorter one this time, fended off by Overton towards the leg side this time.
Flighted one on middle, blocked towards mid on this time.

FOUR BYES! That misses everthing and Paine can't gather that either. A good ball, pitched on off. Overton looks to drive but it sneaks through the bat and through the legs of Paine to the fine leg fence. The boundary brings 150 up for the hosts.
Flatter one on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On the fuller side around off, Buttler looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through backward point for two.

Just short! Shortish and on off, there is extra bounce on this one. Buttler looks to defend but does not get on top of the bounce. It goes off the outside edge but lands short of the third slip fielder. He makes a good stop diving to his left.
Outside off, Buttler makes a leave.
This is angled into the batter, Buttler pushes it to mid on.

Howzzat? The answer to that question is not out. Top stuff though from Cummins. He kept taking it out and now gets it in and a long way. The length is also fuller. Buttler is surprised by it and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down. Going down leg.
On off, Buttler blocks it out.
Fuller and on off, Overton strokes it to mid off.
Good length ball around off, Overton pushes it towards cover and gets off strike.
In the channel on a good length, Buttler does not fiddle with it.
Bouncer around off, Buttler sways away from it.
Swing there but this is too wide for the batter to play. Buttler is not interested.
Fuller around off, Buttler solidly pushes it towards cover.
This is on off and it comes back in. Overton works it to square leg.
One more length ball on off, CO pushes it nicely to mid off.
A sharp short one, Overton ducks under it nicely.
Attacks the off pole again, Overton is solid in defense.

NOT OUT! The impact is outside the line of off stump! There was also a doubt if there was bat involved. In the end, the important thing for England is, Overton survives. Their fans and their pavilion will breathe a big sigh of relief. However, brilliant from Cummins. He once again sets the batter up nicely. After a couple of outswingers, he gets this one to come back in a long way from outside off. Overton seems to have missed it and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal and up goes the finger. Overton signals the 'T' and straightaway says that he has hit that. A huge cheer as the crowd sees the first replay as it seems there is an inside edge. The umpire is not sure as the bat also hits the pad before. Several replays are seen and then, the third umpire is confused and does not have enough evidence to overturn the decision. Time for the Ball Tracker now which shows the impact to be outside off. Once again a huge cheer by the crowd.
A couple to end! This is worked through square leg for two.
Fuller on middle, worked towards mid-wicket for a run.
Fuller ball on off this time, Overton drives it straight to the bowler.
Bumper this time. Overton ducks under it.
FOUR! Brilliantly done! Length ball outside off, Overton leans into the drive and drills this through the covers for a boundary.

Going down the leg side this time as Overton looks to flick. He can not get bat on ball as Paine moves to his left to pouch this one. A muted appeal from behind the wicket but nothing from the bowler.
Fuller outside off, blocked easily towards mid on.
Good length and around off, Buttler opens the face of the bat and guides it to point.
Shorter and outside off, it is left alone.
Another fuller delivery around off, Buttler leans into it and strokes it to covers. A good shot but for no runs.
FOUR! Gets it in the gap this time! Nicely played. This is fuller and outside off, Buttler waits for it and then just opens the face of the bat. Guides it through point and it races away.
Outside off, Buttler is in no mood to play at those.
One more length ball outside off, Buttler does not fiddle with it.
Nicely played in the end! This is flatter and outside off, it stays low. Overton gets his bat down in time and works it to short fine leg.
Tosses it up on off, it is kept out.

A huge appeal from Lyon but not given! This is landed outside off, it turns back in. Overton looks to flick but there seems to be an inside edge onto the pads. It lands short of the diving short leg fielder. Lyon makes a huge shout for an LBW but it is turned down. Warner at leg slip signals there was bat.
Fuller and on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and outside off, Overton initially looks to hit it through the off side but then seeing the turn back in, works it on the leg side.
A dot to end! Shorter and on middle, Overton goes back and looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Left on length again! Shorter and on off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one. Starc needs to go fuller.
Does go full this time, Buttler looks to drive but mistimes it to mid off.
A short one and on middle, Buttler ducks under it. Starc had the shiny part inside, not sure why he bowled it short. He could have got this one shaping back in after taking the last two away.
Takes this one away too and it is fuller on off, Buttler hits it to mid off.
One more delivery outside off, it is left alone.
On off, Buttler defends it solidly.
Outside off and it is in the rough. It comes back in sharply but not enough to make the batter play.
Floats it up on off, it is kept out.
Flighted ball on off, Overton once again manages to block it.
Floats it up on off, Overton manages to keep it out again.
On middle, Overton goes right back and works it on the leg side.
Nicely played! This is bowled outside off, Overton goes back and works it with the turn to short leg. Three maidens in a row.
Very short and on middle, Buttler goes back and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for one.
One more short ball on off, it turns away. It is left alone.

Loud, loud shot! Not given again! This is a lovely delivery. It lands around middle and leg. It pitches and turns away. The batter looks to defend but misses and is hit on the pads. A huge appeal but the umpire shakes his head. The bowler, the skipper and Smith have a chat but then don't review. Rightly so as Ball Tracker shows it to be going over.
One more short one on off, it is whipped through mid-wicket for one.
A googly on off, defended. One ball to go for Lunch.
This is tossed up outside off, Buttler does not play at it. THAT IS TEA ON DAY 5!

Australia celebrate and with such confidence. Dharmsena says no instantly. The Australian celebration ends. Lyon pitches it on middle and gets it to bounce sharply. The ball hits on the abdomen of Overton and lobs straight to the short leg fielder who pouches it and celebrates. Australia do not opt for the review as they probably knew there was no bat involved. They tried to put pressure on the umpire but that didn't work. A top decision.
Fuller this time, Overton looks to drive but is hit on the pads and the ball lobs wide of the silly point fielder.
Flatter this time, blocked off the back foot.
Slightly shorter, worked towards the leg side.
Flatter this time, pushed towards mid-wicket.
This is quicker one on the pads, Overton looked to tickle it fine but misses. The ball lobs off the pads towards Warner at leg slip, he catches it but no appeal from the Australians this time.
Fuller outside off, Buttler blocks it well.
Fuller again, blocked nicely off the front foot.
Bumper outside off, Buttler sways away from it.
Another back of length ball but goes down the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler wanted to play but after seeing the shape away, didn't play.
EDGY FOUR! Fuller ball, Buttler goes for the drive but gets an outside edge. The ball flies wide of the slip cordon and to the third man fence.
Flatter and fuller, kept low as well. Blocked nicely by Overton.
Another solid block from Overton on the off side. This one bounced off the surface from off stump line.
Flatter one outside off, Overton lets it go to the keeper.
Quicker one on middle, worked down the leg side.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Quicker one on the pads, Overton works it down the leg side.
Just outside off, Buttler knows where his off stump is and lets it be.
This is angled into the batter, it lands and then shapes away a long way. Buttler ends up playing  inside the line and gets beaten.
Outside off again, the batter need not play at those.
Slightly shorter, does not bounce a lot. Buttler evades it.
Good length and on off, Buttler guides it to point.
This is angled into the batter, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on middle, it spins down. Overton lets it be.
Loopy ball on off, Overton lunges and keeps it out.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Overton works it to mid-wicket. The fielder fumbles but no runs taken.
A single now as this is worked wide of the fielder at mid-wicket.
Nicely played! Tossed up outside off, it turns back into Buttler and there is extra bounce too. Buttler does well to play it with soft hands on the leg side.
One more dot to end! This is on middle, Buttler works it to short fine leg.
Goes short and on the body, it is pulled down to fine leg for one. Australia on the attack here, a short leg, a silly point and a leg gully in place.

OUT! TIMBER! Nelson strikes for England. He is dismissed on the 111th ball. Is this the Ashes for Australia? They have got the last recognized batsman. A gritty partnership and a gritty knock by Buttler comes to an end. Josh Hazlewood gets the breakthrough. Once again, Australia strike early after the break. Not sure what happened to Buttler there? He has been leaving the ball brilliantly till now. This time though maybe he misreads the length. Josh bowls this very full and it starts just outside off. Comes back in, Buttler shoulders arms to this one. The ball though crashes into the off pole. It turns out to be a bad leave. Buttler is distraught. Australia are ecstatic. Pin-drop silence here. 3 wickets away now are the visitors.
Good length and on middle, this is kept out.

Archer almost kicked the ball onto the stumps. Would have been a comedy of errors. This is on a good length and around off, it comes back in late. Archer looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball falls behind him and ahead of the stumps. Archer looks to kick it away but ends up kicking it on his other leg. The ball then rolls back once again but away from the stumps.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Shorter and outside off, Archer guides it towards gully for one.
Flatter one, pitched on a rough and bounces. Archer looks to fend it off but the ball gets high on him and balloons towards the short leg fielder.
Flighted ball on middle, Archer pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on middle, Jofra comes forward to block but the ball goes off the inside edge towards the leg gully, just short.
This time a solid block from Archer.

OUT! LBW! That's unlucky as long as Archer and England are concerned. Lyon pitches this around off on the rough. The ball has been bouncing high off those roughs but this time it keeps very low. Archer can't do anything about this. He is hit dead on the pads, in front of the stumps. Lyon and Australia appeal. The umpire agrees. Lyon and Australia celebrate. Archer thinks of the review but Overton suggests not to go for it. Archer walks back with a wry smile. Nothing he could've done about this one. Probably not worth reviewing at all. This was a grubber. Barely bounced. What does Ball Tracker show? Impact umpire's call but the ball crashing into the stumps. Review would have been retained but Jofra would have still been out. Just two wickets away are the Australians from retaining the Ashes.
Flatter ball on middle, blocked off the front foot this time.

NOT OUT! FOUR LEG BYES! It indeed is missing leg! Excellent decision by Erasmus. Australia lose one of their reviews. Hazlewood bowls a corker of a yorker. It starts on off and it tails back in. Overton is late in bringing his bat down. The ball goes off the pads and down to the fine leg fence. The Australian players put in a loud appeal in the meantime but it is turned down. Marnus Labuschagne at short leg is extremely confident and indicates to Paine that there is no bat involved and wants it to be reviewed. Paine looks at him, then the bowler and does review. First, the Ultra Edge is checked. No bat. But where is Ball Tracker? Coming, coming, coming, coming, after a full whole minute, it arrives! Impact in line, but missing leg.
Edged but short! Fuller and around off, Overton looks to drive but gets an outside edge which goes on the bounce to the second slip fielder. All of a sudden Overton seems to be struggling.
Good length and on off, Overton defends it.
This is angled into the pads, Overton works it around the corner for one.
BEATEN! This is fuller and outside off, Leach looks to push at it but gets beaten.
Too straight, Leach works it through mid-wicket and takes three. He keeps strike for the next over. Australia won't mind the three.
Cut him into half there! This is shorter and outside off, it jags back in sharply. Goes between the bat and the body of Leach.
BEATEN! This one goes straight on after pitching on a length and outside off. Leach plays inside the line and gets beaten.
Beaten again! This is outside off again. Leach hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
Goes very full and on off, Leach watches it and strokes it to mid off.
A short one on middle, Leach gets on top of the bounce and keeps it out.
Excellently bowled and it is played even better! A yorker, an inswinging one on off. Leach gets his bat down in time and jams it out towards mid on for one.
On the pads, Leach works it to leg slip.
On middle, the batter defends it nicely.
Floats it up around leg pole. Leach is solid in defense again.
Another loopy ball on off, this is kept out.
Floats it up outside off, Leach lunges to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge but lands well short of second slip.
Shorter and outside off, Leach looks to play the late cut but is beaten.
Very full and on middle from around the wicket. It is pushed to the man at mid on.
Slightly fuller and on off, Overton keeps it out.
A short one on middle, the batter stands tall and keeps it out.
One more short one outside off, Overton plays inside the line and lets it through.

EDGY FOUR! This is angled into the batter and it is fuller on off. The ball pitches and moves away. Overton looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge down to the third man fence. Runs needed below 200 but that is immaterial right now. 151 balls left to survive.
Shortish and it is angled into the pads, Overton looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls towards square leg. The batters think of a run but then don't take it.
Good length and on off, Leach keeps it out.
Shorter and on the body, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller but it is outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, Leach looks to flick but misses.
Nicely played again! Fuller and on middle, this is hit to the right of mid on.

That is a gem! Unlucky not to get a wicket there. This is slightly fuller and  just outside off. It comes back in. Leach ends up playing outside the line, the ball sneaks through the gap between bat and pad and goes over the off pole.
On the pads on a good length, clipped towards square leg by Overton for a run.
Bowls a back of length ball outside off. Leach thought of playing it initially but bailed out quickly as this was too wide.

Good length on middle again, Leach is solid in defense. Starc looked at the landing area as soon as he delivered the ball. He looked in some discomfort as he landed bit awkwardly while delivering the ball. He checks his right calf but he is ready to go.
Beaten! This is a superb bouncer and it is closer to the head of Leach. Leach looks to fend it off the back foot but it goes past the gloves of Leach.

FOUR! On the pads on a fullish length of Leach and he crunches this behind square on the leg side for a boundary. The fielder from backward square leg chases the ball but comes second. Some shot that and gets the crowd going as well.
Outside off this time, Leach doesn't fiddle with it.
Good length and around off, Overton plays inside the line, it goes off the outer half towards gully.
Good length again on off, Overton opens the face of the bat and guides it to gully.
Outside off, Overton lets it be.
A short one on the body, Overton ducks under it.
Lovely delivery! This is lands on off and then straightens. Overton does the right thing as he plays the original trajectory but gets beaten.
A solid defense this time to a ball on off.
Goes very full and outside off, it is jammed out to covers.
Outside off, Leach need not play at those.

Comes from around the wicket and angles it into the batter. Leach works it behind square on the leg side, uses the pace of the bowler. The fielder at leg gully runs after it and keeps it down to three.
On the fuller side and on off, Overton defends it nicely.
Attacks the stumps again, Overton easily keeps it out.
Another block and another over goes by! On off, Overton gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
A short one down the leg side, Leach watches it go through to the keeper.

Nasty ball but Leach fends it nicely! A sharp short one on the body, Leach looks to fend it away but takes his eyes off the ball. It hits the glove and then lobs onto the helmet. Falls safely on the off side. Leach takes a breather as he removes his helmet and then his glasses.
One more short one, Leach ducks under it nicely. Cummins gives the batter the stare. That is probably a sign of the Australians getting a little frustrated.
One more short one and it is ducked under again. Time for a yorker now?
No! Goes short again and on the body, Leach pushes it towards mid on and takes one.
This is angled into the batter, Overton pushes it to mid on. Another over played out. 20 more left.
A muted appeal but nothing from the umpire! This lands around leg, Leach looks to flick but misses to get on the pads.
Slower through the air on off, it is kept out.
Another tossed up delivery, Leach is solid in defense once again. A huge cheer as he does so.
One more loud cheer as Leach blocks another delivery which is bowled on middle.
5 balls done in this over too! On the stumps. Blocked.
And Leach plays out the over! This is on the pads, Leach tries to defend but misses to get hit on the pads.
That must have hurt! Overton needs to rub it off! Short and on the body, Craig looks to duck but is late in doing so. Overton gets hit on the arm. He takes his glove off.
One more short one, this time, Overton is ready as he ducks under it.
Third short ball in a row! Overton ducks under it for the second time in a row.
NO BALL! Goes fuller but he has overstepped! Maybe he is pushing too hard, for that extra mile. This is on a length and outside off, Overton looks to defend but is beaten.
One more bumper, Overton sits under it with ease.
Back of a length and on middle, Craig defends it nicely onto the ground.
Good length and on off, Overton manages to defend it nicely again.
Loopy ball on off, the batter prods forward and keeps it out.
Beauty! This is slightly shorter by Lyon and it is quicker. On middle, it pitches and turns away. Goes past the outside edge of Leach's bat.
A little fuller and on middle, Leach blocks it easily.
Slower through the air this time on middle, Leach prods forward and keeps it out.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Slashes and misses! Not sure that shot is needed at the moment. This is shorter and outside off, it skids through. The batter looks to cut but is beaten.
A short one on middle, Overton ducks under it.
Attacks the stumps this time, Overton defends it onto the ground.
Another solid defense! Less than 100 balls left now. Shorter and on off, Overton keeps it out.
Slightly fuller and outside off, the batter lets it be.
Nicely played! This is shorter and around off, it angles away. Overton initially looks to defend but then bails out.
A shorter one on middle, Overton keeps it out nicely.
A leg spinner on middle, Leach looks to flick but it goes off the pads towards short leg. A muted appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Lands it in the rough outside off, this one turns back in sharply. Leach looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Shorter and quicker and on the pads. JL looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Another tossed up ball outside off, Leach keeps it out.

OUT! Catch it... gone! No. 9 is down. This should settle some nerves that was building in the Australian side. Leach's resistance comes to an end. Excellent bowling change by Paine. I had written it is a surprise to many but he has delivered by ending this frustrating stand. A masterstroke by the skipper. Once again, Labuschagne lands it in the rough outside off. It pitches and turns back in sharply. Leach looks to work it on the leg side but due to the extra bounce, it hits the handle and lobs towards Wade who takes it nicely at short leg. Australians are elated. One wicket away now and 91 balls to go.
A full toss, may have caught Broad by surprise. He pushes it back to the bowler.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle again, it is kept out.
Shorter and outside off, the batter goes back and works it to short leg.

Very short! Overton works it down to fine leg. It is going towards the fence. The fielder from square leg jogs after it. The ball though stops near the fence. The batters take only one. Just the two balls to face for Broad.
Negotiates one! This is just outside off, it is left alone.
Loopy ball on off, this one is pushed to covers. Both the balls are played out.
Good length and on middle, this is defended.
A short one and on the body, Overton looks to duck again but the ball hits him on the body. That must have hurt but you need to brush it off and continue.

OUT! LBW! Three reds and Overton is a goner! Marvelous scenes out there as AUSTRALIA HAVE RETAINED THE ASHES! Overton's fighting innings comes to an end. It is Josh Hazlewood who gets the last wicket. A good nut. It lands on off and jags back in. Overton looks to defend but misses to get hit on the front pad. A huge appeal. It looked a touch high but up goes the finger. Overton has no choice but to review. He signals the 'T'. Time for the replays. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows the ball to be hitting the leg pole. Australia continue to celebrate. THEY WIN BY 185 RUNS AND LEAD THE SERIES 2-1!
